column23: Evgeniia: Skipped in Macomber or not imported. Manuscript: https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b100879251/f111.image.r=Ethiopien%20d'Abbadie%20165 Solomon assigned ID 202. This is indeed the best ITool match. However, there is another story with ID 202 in this manuscript, and according to the catalog, these two stories are different (they have different titles, and the second story is matched to another mss, while the first is not). So, it is either Rossini (cataloger) made a mistake, or this story is not ID 202. The catalog title is "l'homme, victime d'un vol, qui battit un tableau de le Vierge". In the English translation of ID 202, there is no "victime d'un vol", but a Jew who lost in a court.

column23: Evgeniia: Catalog title: "le chevalier, qui n'osait, a cause de sa pauvrete, aller a la rencontre de son amile gouvernoeur". Macomber coulnd't choose between ID 203 and 192. In ID 192, there is a friend, althought whether a "young man" is a knight is unclear. https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b10091458z/f132.image. Solomon:The story is matched to 203, but the two incipits of the manuscript CR-Paris 53 differ in the first line of the passage by alteration and reduction. The Macomber ID 203  reads ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ፈረሳዊ፡, but instead of ፈረሳዊ፡ the manuscript CR-Paris 53 reads ክቡር፡ እምሰብአ፡ አፍራስ፡. But in the second line of the sentence they have the same reading. So it is fair to say that it is medieum.  But in any way, it does not match to 192.

column4: The rich knight who was advised by an abbot to pray to Saint Mary to win the heart of the woman with whom he was in love.

The priest from Nārdin who was accused because he kept a nun in his house.
The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
The Arab woman who suffered from an issue of blood for many years and is healed by Mary's icon

The lamp before the icon of Saint Mary that the priest tipped over and yet remained suspended

ʾƎmma Yoḥannǝs and the Ethiopian monk who was on pilgrimage to Jerusalem.
Maryam from Dǝfrā, a child who wanted to receive Communion but was shut up in the house when her family went to church, goes to heaven.
The wife of a pagan official who wished to pray at the Holy Sepulcher is prevented until she is baptized.

The conversion of the Muslim, Rewh, who is renamed Entons Haddis.
The wife of Mark, a priest from Mallawi, is cured of her leprosy.

A Muslim, Katib, tries to extort money from the monks of Saint Anthony.
Homily of John Chrysostom on the visit of Saint Mary and her Son to John the Baptist.
The story of Pifamon, the martyr from Awsim.
The story of John, the martyr from Senhut.

The young novice whom Saint Mary encouraged to persevere in his vocation.
A nun sacristan elopes with a priest, but afterwards they repent.
The bee keeper who consulted a sorceress to have more honey.
The sinful woman who despaired when she kept on sinning and swallowed a scorpion.
The prudent monk who suspected that the food that the monks were eating was harmful, but then saw Saint Mary making it tasty for them.

The rich merchant from Constantinople who lost all his money and made the icon of Saint Mary his guarantor when he borrowed money from a usurer.
The husband who broke his vow that he would live celibately with his wife.
The rich woman who went with the monks to the manbalis for prayer and there saw a vision of Saint Mary.
The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.

column23: The first 33 miracles are the canonical set. After them, another sequence, unusual order and content. Mostly apocryphal legends. Catalog: "la deuxieme partie ... Les recits sont au nombre de 15, mails ils s'ecartent de l'ordre des autres manuscrits avec lesquels ils ne semblent pas toujors s'accorder, meme pour le fond; ils sont presque tous tires de legendes apocryphes de la vie de Marie."

column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ቅምር፡ ክቡረ፡ ዘመድ፡ በስምሰ፡ ክርስቲያናዊ፡ ወኀጢአቱ፡ ዐቢይ፡ እምኀጢአተ፡ ኵሉ፡ ሰብእ፡ ወባዕል፡ ፈድፋደ። ወኢበልዕ፡ እክል፡ ወኢሥጋ፡ ላህም፡ ወእንስሳ። አላ፡ ይበልዕ፡ ሥጋ፡ ሰብእ።...

column23: Evgeniia: The first seven miracles are not described in the catalog (and thus not identified by Macomber). Solomon: there are ony six mirscles!

column4: Thecla cycle: Thecla is taken to Alexandria to see her brother, Abba Esi, in a boat guided by the Archangels Gabriel and Sureyal.
The young man who offered the ring he had received from his girlfriend to the icon of Saint Mary.
The sinful woman who despaired when she kept on sinning and swallowed a scorpion.
The woman who was prevented from fasting by her husband.
The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
The nun who used to pray for the dead, but lost her virginity and died before completing her penance.
The nun whom Saint Mary admonished to recite the Hail Mary more attentively.
Holy Family journey cycle: The king of Egypt asks Saint Mary to bless his land.
The soul of Christina, the wife of Aaron, an Egyptian official, goes to Heaven.
The five sorrows of Saint Mary.
The old woman from Sembat who gave the offering for Saint Mary to Saint George.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Christ celebrates Mass for Saint Mary.
The wife of a pagan official who wished to pray at the Holy Sepulcher is prevented until she is baptized.
The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
Oz, the Byzantine monk, is shown a vision of Hell by Saint Urael.
Archbishop Tilas, who was seized by Jews while carrying a golden chalice.
Abba Mardari, who overheard twelve angels talking about going to Constantinople to hear Saint John Chrysostom praise Saint Mary.
The story of Dilasor, brother of Emperor Theodosius, who was Abba Kiros.
Däbrä Metmaq miracles: The annual apparition of Saint Mary at Däbrä Metmaq (continued)
Saint Mary turns water over which her anaphora was recited by Abba Samuˀel of Wali into miraculous bread.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Saint Mary brings gifts to Abba Samuˀel of Wali.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Satan tries to prevent Abba Samuˀel of Wali from praying by seizing his prayer book.
The husband who denied Christ when he became poor.
Thieves try to steal from a church of Saint Mary in Syria but are unable to bring what they have stolen out of the church.
The Jewish boy who received Holy Communion with his Christian companions.
The only son of a king who dedicated himself to Saint Mary.
The woman from Rome who killed the baby she bore after sleeping with her son
A child whom his mother had vowed to Saint Mary is rescued from drowning.
The two brothers who copied the Miracles of Mary and fell into the doing of a sin.
A knight tries to seduce the wife of a friend, but she is saved by a vision.
The Holy Spirit recounts the salvific events that have occurred on Sunday.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: The Jews go to Bethlehem to seize Saint Mary but are blinded.
The church built on the tomb of Saint Mary that will turn into a ship.
Mareqos, King of Romeya, abandons his throne secretly to become a monk.
Deacon Michael, the grocer and his stolen ring, which Mary helped find in a fish.
Alexander, a Jew from Jerusalem, is delivered three days after he was swallowed up by a dragon.
The pious official who was accused of embezzlement and of having an affair with the wife of his lord.
Saint Mary appears as a winged maiden to John, a monk of Saint Macarius.
The son of a rich official of Cappadocia is raised from the dead.
Saint Mary gives a thirsty dog water to drink from her shoe.
The priest from Cyprus who brought a particle of the Eucharist to a Jew.
The pious mower of hay to whom the gatekeeper gave his daughter in marriage.
The bee keeper who consulted a sorceress to have more honey.
Saint Mary commands a deacon to give Christian burial to a sinful deacon assassinated by his enemies; when they disinter him, a flower is found in his mouth.
When Sefengeya, wife of King Masfeyanos of Romeya, prays to have a child before the icon of Saint Mary, the icon inclines its head; Sefengeya then conceives Yeshaq (Abba Garima).
Daniel from Constantinople, who wanted to go to church to receive Communion even when there was fighting in the streets.
Emperor Honorius, who lived like a monk.
The virgin who sinned with many lovers.
A nun in prison for her faith prays for two virgins.
Mary, Conception of cycle: The conception and nativity of Saint Mary.
Paraleya from Iyyoram, who was beaten by her husband because she was childless.
A hermit in Jerusalem is saved from the temptations of Satan.
A monk, Abraham, drinks poisonous water while on a journey to visit the patriarch and dies, but is then raised from the dead.
The wrath of Saint Mary against the prefect of a church who tried to stop the priests from making a procession while singing hymns to her.
The stone-footed man (i. e., a man with gout) from France.
The two brothers from Rome, Peter, a deacon, and Stephen, an avaricious magistrate.
Pachomius, the avaricious patriarch of Rome, who sold the chrism of the church.
The mighty Goliath threatens to destroy the monastery of Saint Mary.
Emperor Zärˀa Yaˁəqob is given a sign of Badlay's fall.
The priest from Nārdin who was accused because he kept a nun in his house.
Scete miracles: Some of the deceased great Fathers of the Desert appear to the monks of Scete.
The European who wanted to steal the bars of the door to the Manger at Bethlehem.
The avaricious priest who visited a dying man who loved bribes.
The nun who was dissuaded from eloping with a knight by a vision of Hell.
The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.
Däbrä Qaləmon miracles: Abba Samuˀel of Däbrä Qaləmon intercedes for an angel who had disobeyed the command of God.
The church of Saint Mary in Spain to which she used to bring Christian captives.
Sara from Mesot, who became insane and went about naked.
The sinful deacon who was healed by a drop of Saint Mary's milk.
The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
Maryam from Dǝfrā, a child who wanted to receive Communion but was shut up in the house when her family went to church, goes to heaven.
The French artist who fell from the scaffolding while painting frescoes.
Saint Mary carries a dying monk to Jerusalem.
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The pregnant woman who was caught by the tide while going to the church of Saint Michael (Mont Saint Michel)
The thief who was caught stealing from the church of Saint Mary and was released by his captors when he prayed to her.
Saint Mary gives a thirsty dog water to drink from her shoe.
Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam miracles: Message of Saint Mary to Anthony, monk of Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam.
Saint Mary gives a garment to a poor monk.
The daughter of the rich man from Caesarea who could not deliver her baby.
Saint Mary appears as a winged maiden to John, a monk of Saint Macarius.
The hypocritical superior of a monastery who pretended to be religious.
An Egyptian woman comes to Saint Mary in Bethlehem and is healed of her fever.
Holy Family journey cycle: The Holy Family hides from thieves in a sycamore tree at Däbrä Metmaq.
The woman from Cairo whose nine children all died; Mary helped her conceive three more.
The five sorrows of Saint Mary.
The woman from Cairo whose nine children all died; Mary helped her conceive three more.
The five sorrows of Saint Mary.
Oz, the Byzantine monk, is shown a vision of Hell by Saint Urael.
Däbrä Metmaq miracles: The cistern at Däbrä Metmaq is filled miraculously.
Saint Mary gives a garment to a poor monk.
The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
Däbrä Metmaq miracles: Saint Mary shows those assembled at Däbrä Metmaq a negative vision of Mohammad

column4: The monk who saved the church of Saint Mary in Atrib by his prayers when its destruction had been ordered by the Caliph.

column4: John the Evangelist paints an icon of the Crucifixion for Emperor Tiberius.
Däbrä Qaləmon miracles: The events that occurred during the captivity of Abbots Samuˀel of Däbrä Qaləmon and John of Scete.
Saint Alexius lives for fifteen years near a church of Saint Mary in Armenia.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Abba Samuˀel of Wali is lifted up while reciting the Wəddase Maryam.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Saint Mary appears to Abba Samuˀel of Wali and promises blessings to those who drink the water over which they read her anaphora.
Saint Mary turns water over which her anaphora was recited by Abba Samuˀel of Wali into miraculous bread.
Emperor Honorius, who lived like a monk.
An Egyptian woman comes to Saint Mary in Bethlehem and is healed of her fever.
The nun who was dissuaded from eloping with a knight by a vision of Hell.
Saint Mary commands a deacon to give Christian burial to a sinful deacon assassinated by his enemies; when they disinter him, a flower is found in his mouth.
Saint Mary turns water over which her anaphora was recited by Abba Samuˀel of Wali into miraculous bread.
A woman whose right eye had been blinded by a demon is healed by Saint Mary.
Mary, Pregnancy of cycle: Three virgins come to serve Saint Mary as she is about to give birth.
The soul of Christina, the wife of Aaron, an Egyptian official, goes to Heaven.
A priest becomes insane after his entire family dies of the plague.
Mary, Dormition of Cycle: The Dormition and Transitus of Saint Mary. (623, 502, 532, 550 similar)
Mary, Annunciation of cycle: The Annunciation. (297, 435, 536 similar)
The dissolute youth from Ethiopia who was about to be killed by the magistrate.

column4: The story of King Tarses of Fars, who loved to kill Christians.
Sabela, a nun of Caesarea, who had a vision of Saint Mary while sleeping.

column4: The Jew from Rome who wanted to kill Christians, but was seized by the priests of the church of Saint Mary.
The bread and wine that came down from Heaven to Abbot Gabriel during Mass in the church of Saint Mary in Rome.

column23: According to Macomber handlist, this mss has two stories with ID 144, on ff. 19v and 66r. Macomber gave incipits of one of the two stories, but he didn't specify a folio number. So currently both instances have identical incipits in the spreadsheet and the ITool. Catalog doesn't contain miracle records, the mss is online.

column4: Mary, Conception of cycle: The conception and nativity of Saint Mary.
Mary, Conception of cycle: The conception and nativity of Saint Mary.
Mary, Childhood of cycle: When she is three years old, Saint Mary is taken to the Temple. (315, 316-D, 447 similar)
Oz, the Byzantine monk, is shown a vision of Hell by Saint Urael.
Mary, Engagement of cycle: Saint Mary is espoused to Saint Joseph.
A hermit in Jerusalem is saved from the temptations of Satan.
Mary, Pregnancy of: Salome's hands are burned when she tries to verify Saint Mary's virginity, but they are healed when she takes the Christ Child into her arms.
Vision of Theophilus of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family returns from Egypt.
The Jews plot to burn the body of Saint Mary.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: When Tafoneya lays hands on the bier of Saint Mary, an angel cuts his arms off.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays to be taken from this life.
Mary, Assumption of Cycle: The Apostles gather for the funeral of Saint Mary.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint John the Evangelist sees Christ kissing Saint Mary's burial cloth.
Holy Family journey cycle: The rich Egyptian woman who refused to give water to the Holy Family.
A monk, Abraham, drinks poisonous water while on a journey to visit the patriarch and dies, but is then raised from the dead.
The miraculous spring of Mehzab.
Däbrä Metmaq miracles: The annual apparition of Saint Mary at Däbrä Metmaq (continued)
King Bartaqu of Greece, who became a monk.

column4: The Christians gathered for a feast of Saint Mary are saved from the Arabs.
The priest, Rizqallah, recovers things stolen from pilgrims.

Vision of Theophilus of Alexandria (continued): Satan urges Herod to pursue the Holy Family.
Vision of Theophilus of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family returns from Egypt.
The French artist who fell from the scaffolding while painting frescoes.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
Three Arabs, journeying to Rif on the Nile in Egypt, fall into the water due to a storm and two are saved from crocodiles.
Bishop Mercurius, whom the patriarch wanted to remove because of leprosy.
A poor woman with a broken leg is healed by the icon of Saint Mary in the church of Harat ar-Rum.
The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.

Mary, Assumption of cycle: Synaxary entry for 16 Nahase: The Apostles visit Saint Mary in heaven.
The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
The divorced wife who prayed for revenge against her rival.
The husband who broke his vow that he would live celibately with his wife.
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.
Deacon Michael, the grocer and his stolen ring, which Mary helped find in a fish.
The rich man from Colosse who was shot in the eye with an arrow while fighting the Qwez.
The Muslim who found an icon of Saint Mary in his house.

Dabra Qaləmon miracles: The monks of Däbrä Qaləmon who were despoiled by Berbers.
Elizabeth, the blind daughter of Abraham and Gera Anest of Baderman.
The widow who could not find husbands for her three daughters.
The composition of the Maṣḥafa ḥawi by Patriarch Gabriel Ibn Tarīk.
The sinful deacon who was healed by a drop of Saint Mary's milk.
The thief whom the king's soldiers could not kill.
The Emperor of Rome who erected an altar in his palace.
Saint Mary commands a deacon to give Christian burial to a sinful deacon assassinated by his enemies; when they disinter him, a flower is found in his mouth.
The repentant knight who could pray only the Hail Mary.
The bishop for whom Saint Mary tailored a new sackcloth sends a penitent to Santiago.
The deacon's prayer that contained five times "Rejoice!" [tafassehiyat].
Alexander, a Jew from Jerusalem, is delivered three days after he was swallowed up by a dragon.
The pilgrim to Santiago whom Satan persuaded to mutilate himself after falling into a sexual sin.
The priest who could only say the Mass of the Virgin Mary.
The knight who wanted to seduce the daughter of the cobbler.
The Jewish boy who received Holy Communion with his Christian companions.
The pregnant woman who was caught by the tide while going to the church of Saint Michael (Mont Saint Michel)
A man who drowned when a pilgrim ship sank is resuscitated.
The divorced wife who prayed for revenge against her rival.
The woman from Rome whose daughter rose up on the anniversary of her death.
The widow who prayed to Saint Mary and saved her only son from death by hanging.
The sister of Emperor Constantine who prayed to know how Saint Mary bore the Word of God, but then failed to recognize her Son when he appeared to her in church.
The young novice whom Saint Mary encouraged to persevere in his vocation.
The pious official who was accused of embezzlement and of having an affair with the wife of his lord.
The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
The bee keeper who consulted a sorceress to have more honey.
A nun in prison for her faith prays for two virgins.
The woman who was prevented from fasting by her husband.
The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
The rich merchant from Constantinople who lost all his money and made the icon of Saint Mary his guarantor when he borrowed money from a usurer.
The husband who broke his vow that he would live celibately with his wife.
Saint Mary saves the soul of a rich sinner who had repented and was planning to build a monastery and become a monk.
The two blessed monks, Sadaqā and ʾƎstifānos, from the monastery of Saint Victor (Fiqǝṭor); Mary punishes those who steal from and attack them.
Pachomius, the avaricious patriarch of Rome, who sold the chrism of the church.
The avaricious priest who visited a dying man who loved bribes.
The nun who was dissuaded from eloping with a knight by a vision of Hell.
The shepherd near the church of Saint Paul in Rome who was possessed by a demon.
The monk who has carried by the bretheren to church when he became too sick to walk.
A ship that was about to founder is saved when they pray to Saint Mary.
The Jew who attacked the icon of Saint Mary when he failed to obtain by litigation someone else's property.
The knight who denied Christ at the bidding of Satan, in order to have fine clothes for a reception, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
The monk who was custodian of a church near a river and drowned while trying to cross to visit his lover.
The nun who used to pray for the dead, but lost her virginity and died before completing her penance.
The nun whom Saint Mary admonished to recite the Hail Mary more attentively.
The monk who saved the church of Saint Mary in Atrib by his prayers when its destruction had been ordered by the Caliph.
Abba Mardari, who overheard twelve angels talking about going to Constantinople to hear Saint John Chrysostom praise Saint Mary.
The wealthy man to whom Saint Mary appeared in the form of a bird to save the countryside from pestilence.
Nəkʷal, the deacon from Margawkim, who spent his master’s money on the poor.
Maryam from Dǝfrā, a child who wanted to receive Communion but was shut up in the house when her family went to church, goes to heaven.
The devout Muslim who became a Christian when Saint Mary appeared to him.
Däbrä Metmaq miracles: Yeshaq, prior of Däbrä Metmaq, who fled to Scete, Egypt, to escape the burden of his office.
The priest from Cyprus who brought a particle of the Eucharist to a Jew.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ነዳይ፡ ቀሲስ፡ በሀገረ፡ ቆጵሮስ፡ ወአልቦቱ፡ ምንተኒ፡ እምሲሳየ፡ ዕለት። ወሶበ፡ ጸንዐ፡ ላዕሌሁ፡ ንዲት፡ ወረኅብ፡ ሖረ፡ ኀበ፡ አሐዱ፡ አይሁዳዊ፡ ወተለቅሐ፡ እምኔሁ፡ ሠለስተ፡ ምእተ፡ ዲናረ

column4: Thieves try to steal from a church of Saint Mary in Syria but are unable to bring what they have stolen out of the church.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ በሀገረ፡ ሻም፡ ዘተሐንጸት፡ በስማ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወባቲ፡ ንዋይ፡ ብዙኃ። ወበአሐቲ፡ እምመዋዕል፡ ተማከሩ፡ ፈያት፡ ከመ፡ ይሥርቁ፡ ንዋየ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን

column4: A child whom his mother had vowed to Saint Mary is rescued from drowning.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘተሐንጸት፡ በስመ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. በሀገረ፡ ወርወራ፡ እምአድያመ፡ ግብጽ፡ በጽንፈ፡ ባሕር፡ ወባቲ፡ ህየ፡ መዕዳወ፡ ከመ፡ የዓድው፡ ባቲ፡ ሰብእ፡ ወእንስሳ

column4: Däbrä Metmaq miracles: Saint Mary shows those assembled at Däbrä Metmaq a negative vision of Mohammad
Some Christians held captive by a Muslim are freed by an angel and are brought to Cyprus.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ እስላም፡ በምድረ፡ ምዕራብ፡ ርኁቅ፡ እምሀገረ፡ ቆጵሮስ፡ መጠነ፡ ዕስራ፡ ዕለት፡ ወሖረ፡ ከመ፡ ይጸብዖሙ፡ ለክርስቲያን፡ በከመ፡ ልማዱ

column4: A thief is hanged upside down with the objects he stole from the church of Saint Mary in Sebkahad.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ በሀገረ፡ ግብጽ፡ ዘተሐንጸት፡ በስመ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ወስማ፡ ለሀገር፡ ስብከሐድ። ወበአሐቲ፡ እምመዋዕል፡ መጽኡ፡ ሠረቅት፡ ወቦኡ፡ በሌሊት፡ ወሰበሩ፡ መሰከወ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን

When Satan destroys the oven of a monastery, he is compelled to serve the monks for twelve years in punishment.

The mighty Goliath threatens to destroy the monastery of Saint Mary.
The cupbearer of the king of France.

The peasant who became rich from other people's goods.
The young man who was ready to serve Satan, but refused to deny Saint Mary.

Saint Mary appears to Yohannes Kama.
The two brothers who copied the Miracles of Mary and fell into the doing of a sin.
A priest is warned by an angel not to rush when incensing the icon of Saint Mary.
The Arab woman who suffered from an issue of blood for many years and is healed by Mary's icon
The lamp before the icon of Saint Mary that the priest tipped over and yet remained suspended

The man who accepted fine clothes as a bribe for future favors.

The sinful woman who despaired when she kept on sinning and swallowed a scorpion.
The composition of the Wǝddāse Maryam by the Syrian potter.

column4: The priest, Rizqallah, recovers things stolen from pilgrims.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Synaxary entry for 16 Nahase: The Apostles visit Saint Mary in heaven.
The rich knight who was advised by an abbot to pray to Saint Mary to win the heart of the woman with whom he was in love.
The pious mower of hay to whom the gatekeeper gave his daughter in marriage.
The Christians gathered for a feast of Saint Mary are saved from the Arabs.

Vision of Theophilus of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family returns from Egypt.
The French artist who fell from the scaffolding while painting frescoes.
The five sorrows of Saint Mary.
The hungry man whom Saint Mary used to feed.
The rich man who threw dry bread to a beggar in the name of Saint Mary.
The man who would not eat before receiving Holy Communion.
The sister of Emperor Constantine who prayed to know how Saint Mary bore the Word of God, but then failed to recognize her Son when he appeared to her in church.
The merchant who distributed as alms the money that had been loaned him by a friend.
The two brothers from Rome, Peter, a deacon, and Stephen, an avaricious magistrate.
The nun who was dissuaded from eloping with a knight by a vision of Hell.
The dog that ran off with a manuscript of the Miracles of Mary.

column4: Saint Basil cycle: The proud men who wanted to have a splendid icon of Saint Mary made.
The virgin who sinned with many lovers.
The man who was possessed by a spirit of epilepsy [nagargar] for 47 years.
The brigands who killed each other at the miraculous spring.
The only son of a king who dedicated himself to Saint Mary.
The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
Maryam from Dǝfrā, a child who wanted to receive Communion but was shut up in the house when her family went to church, goes to heaven.
Saint Mary carries a dying monk to Jerusalem.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
Three Arabs, journeying to Rif on the Nile in Egypt, fall into the water due to a storm and two are saved from crocodiles.
The church of Saint Mary that moved by itself to the shore of the Mediterranean Sea.
The story of the blind priest, Yohannes Bakansi; Mary heals his eyes with milk from her breasts
The rich man from Colosse who was shot in the eye with an arrow while fighting the Qwez.
The widow who could not find husbands for her three daughters.
The two brothers who copied the Miracles of Mary and fell into the doing of a sin.
Saint Mary appears to the martyr, Giyorgis Haddis, in prison.
Katir, the old priest from Elkesus, who was about to be dismissed from the church.
The story of the two brothers from Dalga who were dyers.
The stone-footed man (i. e., a man with gout) from France.
Bishop Mercurius, whom the patriarch wanted to remove because of leprosy.
A poor woman with a broken leg is healed by the icon of Saint Mary in the church of Harat ar-Rum.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.

The story of the cannibal from Qemer.

The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.
The five sorrows of Saint Mary.
The reopening of the church in Harat Zuwayla.
Deacon Michael, the grocer and his stolen ring, which Mary helped find in a fish.

Däbrä Qaləmon miracles: Abba Samuˀel of Däbrä Qaləmon intercedes for an angel who had disobeyed the command of God.
Holy Family journey cycle: The rich Egyptian woman who refused to give water to the Holy Family.
column15: ወኮነ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ነገር፡ እምድኅረ፡ ወለደቶ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወአዘዘ፡ ሄሮድስ፡ ከመ፡ ይቅትሉ፡ ሕፃናተ፡ ዘክልኤ፡ ዓማት። ወሰሚዓ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ አጐየየቶ፡ ለፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡ ውስተ፡ ምድረ፡ ግብጽ። ወእንዘ፡ ትትጐየይ፡ ወአብጽሐቶ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ እምአህጉረ፡ ግብጽ፡ ኃምስ፡ ወአኃዞ፡ ለፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡ ጽምዓ፡ ማይ፡ እስመ፡ ጊዜ፡ ቀትር፡ ውእቱ። ወቦአት፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ከመ፡ ትስእል፡ ማየ፡ ለፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ወሀቤ፡ ዝናማት፡ ወይእቲሰ፡ ብእሲት፡ ባዕልት፡ ጥቀ፡ እምንዋየ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ዓለም፡ ወበምግባረ፡ ኀጢአት፡ ወነዳይት፡ ይእቲ፡ በምግባረ፡ ሠናይ፡ ወድርክት፡ ይእቲ፡ ካልእታ፡ ለኤልዛቤል
column23: This mss has two stories with ID 321, on ff. 36v and 100r. Macomber gave incipits of one of the two stories, but he didn't specify a folio number. So currently both instances have identical incipits in the spreadsheet and the ITool. According to catalog, it seems the stories are not different (but neither is said to be a recopying). The manuscript is online.

column4: The composition of the Wǝddāse Maryam by the Syrian potter.
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The rich merchant from Constantinople who lost all his money and made the icon of Saint Mary his guarantor when he borrowed money from a usurer.
The daughter of the chief of the thieves is cured of her leprosy at the miraculous spring.
Saint Mary saves the soul of a thief who was slain by the miraculous spring.
The deacon's prayer that contained five times "Rejoice!" [tafassehiyat].
The thief whom the king's soldiers could not kill.
Saint Mary commands a deacon to give Christian burial to a sinful deacon assassinated by his enemies; when they disinter him, a flower is found in his mouth.
The knight who denied Christ at the bidding of Satan, in order to have fine clothes for a reception, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
The nun whom Saint Mary admonished to recite the Hail Mary more attentively.
A man who drowned when a pilgrim ship sank is resuscitated.
The sinful deacon who was healed by a drop of Saint Mary's milk.
The story of the blind priest, Yohannes Bakansi; Mary heals his eyes with milk from her breasts
The rich knight who was advised by an abbot to pray to Saint Mary to win the heart of the woman with whom he was in love.
The monk who has carried by the bretheren to church when he became too sick to walk.
The pious mower of hay to whom the gatekeeper gave his daughter in marriage.
A herdsman saves his beasts in a storm by praying to Saint Mary.
The monk who was custodian of a church near a river and drowned while trying to cross to visit his lover.
The Muslim who found an icon of Saint Mary in his house.
The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
The widow who could not find husbands for her three daughters.
The story of the two brothers from Dalga who were dyers.
The faded icon of Saint Mary that the mother-in-law wanted to discard.
The son of a rich official of Cappadocia is raised from the dead.
The rich woman who went with the monks to the manbalis for prayer and there saw a vision of Saint Mary.
The lamp before the icon of Saint Mary that the priest tipped over and yet remained suspended
The monk who saved the church of Saint Mary in Atrib by his prayers when its destruction had been ordered by the Caliph.
The Christians gathered for a feast of Saint Mary are saved from the Arabs.
The priest, Rizqallah, recovers things stolen from pilgrims.
Saint Mary appears during Mass in the church at Meneta Sard.
The story of the martyr, Saint Victor, and his mother, Martha.
The Arab woman who entrusted her jewels to a Christian for safekeeping.
A hermit in Jerusalem is saved from the temptations of Satan.
Thecla cycle: Thecla is taken to Alexandria to see her brother, Abba Esi, in a boat guided by the Archangels Gabriel and Sureyal.
The son of the Muslim ruler of Egypt blasphemes the icon of Saint Mary.
Mareqos, King of Romeya, abandons his throne secretly to become a monk.
The people of Romeya appeal to Patriarch Dionysius to find King Mareqos.
When Sefengeya, wife of King Masfeyanos of Romeya, prays to have a child before the icon of Saint Mary, the icon inclines its head; Sefengeya then conceives Yeshaq (Abba Garima).
Arabs try to plunder the monasteries of Egypt during the famine of 1120 MM [likely 1404 CE]
Three Arabs, journeying to Rif on the Nile in Egypt, fall into the water due to a storm and two are saved from crocodiles.
The story of the blind priest, Yohannes Bakansi; Mary heals his eyes with milk from her breasts
Katir, the old priest from Elkesus, who was about to be dismissed from the church.
The rich man who threw dry bread to a beggar in the name of Saint Mary.
The daughter of the rich man from Caesarea who could not deliver her baby.
Holy Family journey cycle: The people of an Egyptian town set fierce dogs on the Holy Family.
Holy Family journey cycle: The rich Egyptian woman who refused to give water to the Holy Family.

column4: Holy Family journey cycle: The inhabitants of an Egyptian town who plot to hand Jesus over to King Herod are turned into animals.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Christ celebrates Mass for Saint Mary.
The church of Saint Mary in Spain to which she used to bring Christian captives.
The woman from Cairo whose nine children all died; Mary helped her conceive three more.
The hungry man whom Saint Mary used to feed.
The nominal Christian from Sidon who encountered a dragon.
The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
The two brothers from Rome, Peter, a deacon, and Stephen, an avaricious magistrate.
Pachomius, the avaricious patriarch of Rome, who sold the chrism of the church.
The avaricious priest who visited a dying man who loved bribes.
The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
Maryam from Dǝfrā, a child who wanted to receive Communion but was shut up in the house when her family went to church, goes to heaven.
The French artist who fell from the scaffolding while painting frescoes.
Saint Mary carries a dying monk to Jerusalem.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
Three Arabs, journeying to Rif on the Nile in Egypt, fall into the water due to a storm and two are saved from crocodiles.
The church of Saint Mary that moved by itself to the shore of the Mediterranean Sea.
The story of the blind priest, Yohannes Bakansi; Mary heals his eyes with milk from her breasts
The rich man from Colosse who was shot in the eye with an arrow while fighting the Qwez.
Elizabeth, the blind daughter of Abraham and Gera Anest of Baderman.
The widow who could not find husbands for her three daughters.
The two brothers who copied the Miracles of Mary and fell into the doing of a sin.
Saint Mary appears to the martyr, Giyorgis Haddis, in prison.
Katir, the old priest from Elkesus, who was about to be dismissed from the church.
The story of the two brothers from Dalga who were dyers.
The stone-footed man (i. e., a man with gout) from France.
Bishop Mercurius, whom the patriarch wanted to remove because of leprosy.
A poor woman with a broken leg is healed by the icon of Saint Mary in the church of Harat ar-Rum.
The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
The deacon's prayer that contained five times "Rejoice!" [tafassehiyat].
Dabra Qaləmon miracles: The monk of Dabra Qaləmon who humbly pretends not to fast and is saved from his brothers by Mary.
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The widow who prayed to Saint Mary and saved her only son from death by hanging.
The pregnant woman who was caught by the tide while going to the church of Saint Michael (Mont Saint Michel)
The virgin who sinned with many lovers.
The woman from Rome whose daughter rose up on the anniversary of her death.
The only son of a king who dedicated himself to Saint Mary.
The sister of Emperor Constantine who prayed to know how Saint Mary bore the Word of God, but then failed to recognize her Son when he appeared to her in church.
The shepherd near the church of Saint Paul in Rome who was possessed by a demon.
The divorced wife who prayed for revenge against her rival.
The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.
The daughter of the chief of the thieves is cured of her leprosy at the miraculous spring.
Saint Basil cycle: The proud men who wanted to have a splendid icon of Saint Mary made.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
Mary, Nativity of cycle: Saint Mary heals the daughter of Arsaban while still in the womb of Saint Anne.
A container of oil remains suspended in mid air in a church of Saint Mary when the cord by which it was suspended breaks.
The monk who was expelled from school when he could not pay his teacher.
The new tabot of Saint Mary that was found outside the box in which it had been placed.
A monk, while guarding a church, has a nocturnal emission and finds himself suddenly outside the courtyard of the church.
The thieves who stole the furnishings of a church of Saint Mary and refused to restore them when she appeared to them.
A young monk is horrified when he has a sexual dream.
Saint Mary visits Calvary.
Homily on the greatness of Saint Mary.
A Christian retainer escapes unharmed when his king is defeated by the Muslims.
The woman who was crossing a river on a raft [mezlal].
The milk of Saint Mary that was poured on the ground in Egypt.
King Dawit (1382-1413) miracles: Saint Mary makes a covenant with King Dawit of Ethiopia.
King Dawit  (1382-1413) miracles: The general of King (Dawit) of Ethiopia who defected to the enemy.
The man who lost a slave that he was about to sell in Barara.
The carpenter who asked for a copy of the Gadla samaˁtat as a reward for his services in building a church.
The icon of Saint Mary in a church of Alexandria that some Europeans tried to steal.
Giyorgis's writing: The abbot who rejected the horologium and other works of Abba Giyorgis.
Giyorgis's writing: Saint Mary cuts short her visit to a pious monk when she hears her name invoked according to the horologium of Abba Giyorgis.
Holy Family journey cycle: Saint Mary is welcomed when she returns to Galilee.
A container of oil remains suspended in mid air in a church of Saint Mary when the cord by which it was suspended breaks.
The man who wanted to give a banquet on Saint Mary's feast but was unable because of a famine.
Christ gives Ethiopia as tithes to Saint Mary.
The composition of the Maṣḥafa ḥawi by Patriarch Gabriel Ibn Tarīk.
The wife of Joseph from Mǝneta Diyāqon, who had no male children.
Amnut, the custodian of a church in Egypt, quarrels with his bishop.
The story of the sorcerers Taludar, who was possessed by a demon.
Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam miracles: The infidel who stole the lumber from the church at Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam.
The story of John, the martyr from Senhut.
Scete miracles: Emperor Zeno builds churches in Scete.
The story of Michael, the scribe who converted to Islam when he was beaten.
A monk, Abraham, drinks poisonous water while on a journey to visit the patriarch and dies, but is then raised from the dead.
Homily on the miracles of Saint Mary.
The persecution of the Christians during the patriarchate of Cosmas II.
Emperor Arcadius and the golden statue of Saint Mary; he asks Saint John Chrysostom to expound on Matthew 1: 25.
Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil and the Jewish merchant of Caesarea who stole a golden plate from the church, but later became a Christian.
The election of Patriarch Matthew I.
Holy Family journey cycle: The places in Egypt visited by the Holy Family.
The prodigal son of a man who used, when he was alive, to feed two persons; Saint Mary promises him riches, but he finds only two grains of gold.
King Bartaqu of Greece, who became a monk.
A dragon that had swallowed up Efrem, a monk of Däbrä Timona, is compelled to vomit him up alive ten days later.
The woman whose baby daughter was carried off by a hyena.
The woman who was falsely accused of killing the child she was nursing and was condemned to death.
Barnabas from Sandafa, who used to venerate Saint Mary's icon.
A barren woman conceives and bears salda Masqal.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ መካን፡ ወይዘነጕጓ፡ ብእሲሃ፡ ወይጸርፋ፡ ብዙኃ፡ ጊዜያት። ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ በጥቃ፡ ቤታ፡ ወትገይስ፡ በሌሊት፡ ከመ፡ ኢያእምራ፡ ብእሲሃ፡ ወትስእላ፡ በብካይ

column4: Saint Mary receives the Pact of Mercy (kidan mehret) (Synaxary entry for the 16th of Yakkatit). (470, 553, 632 similar)
column23: The miracle continues on f. 103r (according to Macomber handlist)

column4: Zärˀa Yaˁəqob miracles:  Zärˀa Yaˁəqob and the invasion of Badlay.
Emperor Zärˀa Yaˁəqob is given a sign of Badlay's fall.
The beggar at the church of Qirqos in Amhara from whose head a horn grew.
Saint Mary appears to the gabaz of her church in Waybela and tells him about the fall of Badlay.
King Dawit miracles: The miracle concerning the golden ink during the reign of King Dawit.
Saints Mary and Gabriel visit an Ethiopian named Gabra Maryam and heal him.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በብሔረ፡ ኢትዮጵያ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወዓማፂ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ወባሕቱ፡ ኮነ፡ ያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወይገብር፡ ተዝካራ፡ ወካልዕሰ፡ አልቦቱ፡ ምግባረ፡ ሠናይ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ አሚነ፡ ወልዳ፡ ወአፍቅሮ፡ ዚአሃ። ወኮነ፡ በአሐዱ፡ እምመዋዕል፡ በሰንበተ፡ እኁድ፡ ኃደረ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያና፡ እንዘ፡ ይዌድሳ፡ ወይጼብሓ፡ ወይገኒ፡ ለነግሣ

column4: Sara from Mesot, who became insane and went about naked.
Archbishop Tilas, who was seized by Jews while carrying a golden chalice.
Elias from Elkesus, who was falsely accused and was suspended by the abbot.
The story of Dilasor, brother of Emperor Theodosius, who was Abba Kiros.
Mary, Nativity of cycle: The birth of Saint Mary on the first of Genbot.
Mary, Pregnancy of cycle: Saint Mary is found to be pregnant.
Mary, Annunciation of cycle: The Annunciation. (297, 435, 536 similar)
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Christ orders Abba Samu'el of Wali to celebrate Mass for the feast of Saint Mary.
Abraham, a relative of Saint Stephen, becomes a Christian.
column15: ወኮነ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ቅዱስ፡ እምዘመዱ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ እስጢፋኖስ፡ እምነገደ፡ ሌዊ፡ እምኢየሩሳሌም፡ ወኮነ፡ ስሙ፡ ለአቡሁ፡ አብርሃም፡ ወልደ፡ ሌዊ፡ ወልደ፡ ዮሴፍ፡ እኁሁ፡ ለስምዖን፡ እኁሁ፡ ለእመ፡ እስጢፋኖስ፡ ወበጊዜ፡ ልደቱ፡ ሰመይዎ፡ ስመ፡ አቡሁ

column4: Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Abba Samuˀel of Wali is lifted up while reciting the Wəddase Maryam.
The Jew from Rome who wanted to kill Christians, but was seized by the priests of the church of Saint Mary.
King Yasay of Egypt, who became a monk in Däbrä Rom.
Patriarch Tewoqritos of Jerusalem rebukes King Akratis of Egypt for not fasting or praying.
Deganna, the church builder, who was asked by King Aktab to build a temple for his pagan gods.
The story of Astaqaˀos, the European potter who was buried alive.
Emperor Honorius, who lived like a monk.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: At the commemoration of Abba Samuˀel of Wali a blind man recovers his sight.
column15: ወእምድኅረ፡ ዕረፍቱ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ በ፵፡ ዕለት፡ ተጋብኡ፡ ሕዝብ፡ ከመ፡ ይግበሩ፡ ተዝካሮ፡ ኀበ፡ መቃብሪሁ፡ ዘምስለ፡ ቀሳውስት፡ ወዲያቆናት፡ ወመነኮሳት፡ ወመኳንንት፡ እድ፡ ወአንስት፡ እስከ፡ ይከይዱ፡ ቢጾሙ

column4: Samuˀel of Wali miracles: A blind woman is brought by her son to the tomb of Abba Samuˀel of Wali.

column4: Paraleya from Iyyoram, who was beaten by her husband because she was childless.

The mighty Goliath threatens to destroy the monastery of Saint Mary.
The Muslim who found an icon of Saint Mary in his house.
The only son of a king who dedicated himself to Saint Mary.
The young man who was ready to serve Satan, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
The merchant who distributed as alms the money that had been loaned him by a friend.
Pachomius, the avaricious patriarch of Rome, who sold the chrism of the church.
The monk custodian of the church who prayed to see Saint Mary.
The bankrupt merchant to whom Satan offered two pearls if he would deny Christ and Saint Mary.

The Jewish cowherd who was baptized by his Christian companions.
The bee keeper who consulted a sorceress to have more honey.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.

The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.

A knight tries to seduce the wife of a friend, but she is saved by a vision.
The hypocritical superior of a monastery who pretended to be religious.

The peasant who became rich from other people's goods.

The monk who got himself appointed abbot of another monastery by the king, without the consent of the monks.
The young man who offered the ring he had received from his girlfriend to the icon of Saint Mary.
A ship that was about to founder is saved when they pray to Saint Mary.
The Jew who attacked the icon of Saint Mary when he failed to obtain by litigation someone else's property.
The knight who denied Christ at the bidding of Satan, in order to have fine clothes for a reception, but refused to deny Saint Mary.

column4: The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.
The sinful deacon who was healed by a drop of Saint Mary's milk.
The thief whom the king's soldiers could not kill.
Saint Mary commands a deacon to give Christian burial to a sinful deacon assassinated by his enemies; when they disinter him, a flower is found in his mouth.
The repentant knight who could pray only the Hail Mary.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
The bishop for whom Saint Mary tailored a new sackcloth sends a penitent to Santiago.
The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
The nun who used to pray for the dead, but lost her virginity and died before completing her penance.
The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
The church of Saint Mary that moved by itself to the shore of the Mediterranean Sea.

column4: Saint Mary assists Abba Daniel in the desert and gives him a lion to ride on.
The European monk, Zena Krəstos, who was a herder and whose beasts were attacked by a lion.
Saints Michael and Gabriel appear while Abbot Eliab is teaching his monks, who are given bread from Heaven.
Homily of Saint John the Evangelist on the greatness of Saint Mary, which he had seen in a vision.
Pelagia, a nun from Caesarea, whom Satan afflicted with leprosy.
The monastery near Alexandria whose trees were cut down by Jews.
Aqlemeya, a poor woman from Rome, who was tied to a tree by brigands for five days and nights.
Sabela, a nun of Caesarea, who had a vision of Saint Mary while sleeping.
The bread and wine that came down from Heaven to Abbot Gabriel during Mass in the church of Saint Mary in Rome.
Bishop Deraleyos in Däbrä Gass, who was a lazy monk.
The European Archbishop Thaddeus, whom Saint Mary assisted at Mass.
The monk, Abiathar, in Nubia, who was led to repentance by a vision of Saint Mary.
Eusebius, whom Saint Mary took to Heaven.
The story of the martyr, Saint Romanus.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ሮማኖስ፡ በደወለ፡ ግብጽ፡ አዳም፡ ስነ፡ ራእዩ፡ ወመንክር፡ ኂሩታቲሁ፡ ወሠናይ፡ በኵሉ፡ ግዕዙ፡ ወያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወበአሐዱ፡ ዕለት፡ እንዘ፡ ሀሎ፡ በውስተ፡ ጸሎቱ፡ አኃዞ፡ ደቃስ፡ ወመጽአት፡ ኀቤሁ፡ እግዝእትነ

column4: The prophet, Jonah, who came from Egypt.
Matthias, a student from Bartos in Egypt, who was beaten and imprisoned for teaching about Christ.
How the angels worship the Eucharist, the Cross and Saint Mary.

column4: Sara from Mesot, who became insane and went about naked.
Arkaledes from Qawep, who vowed not to look again at a woman, when his mother came to visit him, he died before seeing her.
Vision granted to Archbishop Bartholomew in Jerusalem.
Four thieves break into the church of Saint Mary and steal vestments; they are brought back by lions.
Scete miracles: Abbot Tasfa Mahebar from Caesarea, who was given a cloud as a chariot and went to visit Abba Zakkareyas in Scete.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ አበ፡ ምኔት፡ በሀገረ፡ ቂሳርያ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ተስፋ፡ ማኅበር፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወይዌድሶ፡ ፍጹመ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር። ወወሀበቶ፡ ደመና፡ ከመ፡ ይኵኖ፡ ሠረገላ፡ ወከመ፡ ይሑር፡ ኀበ፡ ፈቀደ

column4: The soul of Christina, the wife of Aaron, an Egyptian official, goes to Heaven.
When a couple tries to marry their son whom they had dedicated to Saint Mary, he falls sick to the point of death.
When Pariqos of Fesa confesses his sins to the bishop, the latter, refusing him absolution, tells him to go to Abba Yaceqob (Santiago).
Bishop Hildephonsus sees the icon of Saint Mary sweating; she asks him to raise a girl from the dead.
The election of Patriarch Matthew I.
The woman whose baby daughter was carried off by a hyena.
A plague in a monastery is halted at the prayer of a monk.
A child whom his mother had vowed to Saint Mary is rescued from drowning.
Doyq, the son of Taliq, is raised from the dead by Saint Mary while she was still in the womb of Saint Anne.

column4: The story of Abadir, a district governor of Egypt.
Saint Mary asks bread from a poor widow during the flight from Herod.
Saint Mary asks bread from a poor widow during the flight from Herod.
Mary, Dormition of cycle: Certain ones raised from the dead relate to Saint Mary their sufferings in the fires of Gehenna.

Saladdin and his men try to force their way into the house where Saint Mary was born.

column4: Saint Mary teaches a man who had been refused instruction how to write.

column4: Holy Family journey cycle: The king of Egypt asks Saint Mary to bless his land.

Emperor Zärˀa Yaˁəqob is given a sign of Badlay's fall.

Mary, Pregnancy of cycle: Saint Mary is found to be pregnant.
Christ, Nativity of cycle: How the Virgin Mary gave birth (see no. 299) (347, 445 similar)
Christ, Nativity of cycle: The magi and their chief, Balaam, see the star of Christ's birth.
Saint Mary comes to a church in the form of a white dove to heal from smallpox a man whose only good work was celebrating her commemoration.

column4: Mary, Dormition of Cycle: Dormition and Assumption of Saint Mary's body into Heaven.  (623, 502, 532, 550 similar)

column4: The church of Saint Mary in Spain to which she used to bring Christian captives.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Abba Samuˀel of Wali is lifted up while reciting the Wəddase Maryam.
Mary, Annunciation of cycle: The Annunciation. (297, 435, 536 similar)
The composition of the Maṣḥafa ḥawi by Patriarch Gabriel Ibn Tarīk.
Amnut, the custodian of a church in Egypt, quarrels with his bishop.
The priest from Nārdin who was accused because he kept a nun in his house.
Yoḥannǝs finds a copy of the acts of Saints Juliana and Barbara that he had lost.
The wife of Joseph from Mǝneta Diyāqon, who had no male children.
Scete miracles: Eulogius, the stonemason of Scete, Egypt, who used to give hospitality to strangers.
The old woman from Sembat who gave the offering for Saint Mary to Saint George.
The conversion of a Muslim merchant who had been imprisoned in Naples.
The story of the sorcerers Taludar, who was possessed by a demon.
Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam miracles: The infidel who stole the lumber from the church at Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam.
The conversion of the Muslim, Rewh, who is renamed Entons Haddis.
Homily of John Chrysostom on the visit of Saint Mary and her Son to John the Baptist.
The story of John, the martyr from Senhut.
Scete miracles: Saint Mary blesses Scete, which Saint Macarius chooses for his monastery.
The story of Michael, the scribe who converted to Islam when he was beaten.
A monk, Abraham, drinks poisonous water while on a journey to visit the patriarch and dies, but is then raised from the dead.
The wrath of Saint Mary against the prefect of a church who tried to stop the priests from making a procession while singing hymns to her.
Homily on the miracles of Saint Mary.
The persecution of the Christians during the patriarchate of Cosmas II.
Emperor Arcadius and the golden statue of Saint Mary; he asks Saint John Chrysostom to expound on Matthew 1: 25.
The beggar at the church of Qirqos in Amhara from whose head a horn grew.
The merchant from Senfewat who struck the icon of Saint Mary.
King Dawit miracles: The miracle concerning the golden ink during the reign of King Dawit.
Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil and the Jewish merchant of Caesarea who stole a golden plate from the church, but later became a Christian.
The election of Patriarch Matthew I.
Holy Family journey cycle: The places in Egypt visited by the Holy Family.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Abba Samuˀel of Wali is lifted up while reciting the Wəddase Maryam.
Christ, Nativity of cycle: How the Virgin Mary gave birth (see no. 299) (347, 445 similar)
Saint Mary heals two women whom a demon had made ill.

column4: Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil and the Jewish merchant of Caesarea who stole a golden plate from the church, but later became a Christian.
The conversion of a Muslim merchant who had been imprisoned in Naples.
Mary, Annunciation of cycle: The Annunciation. (297, 435, 536 similar)
The priest from Nārdin who was accused because he kept a nun in his house.
The wrath of Saint Mary against the prefect of a church who tried to stop the priests from making a procession while singing hymns to her.
The abbot who did not allow the Miracles of Mary to be read in his monastery.
Emperor Honorius, who lived like a monk.
Mary, Conception of cycle: The conception and nativity of Saint Mary.
Mary, Childhood of cycle: Saint Mary stays in the Temple. (315, 316-D, 447 similar)
Oz, the Byzantine monk, is shown a vision of Hell by Saint Urael.
Mary, Engagement of cycle: Saint Mary is espoused to Saint Joseph.
Mary, Pregnancy of: Salome's hands are burned when she tries to verify Saint Mary's virginity, but they are healed when she takes the Christ Child into her arms.
The Jews plot to burn the body of Saint Mary.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint John the Evangelist sees Christ kissing Saint Mary's burial cloth.
A monk, Abraham, drinks poisonous water while on a journey to visit the patriarch and dies, but is then raised from the dead.
King Bartaqu of Greece, who became a monk.
Däbrä Qaləmon miracles: Abba Samuˀel of Däbrä Qaləmon instructs his disciples on his deathbed.
The story of Saint Alexius [Abdo l a-Masih], son of Emperor Theodosius.
The healing of the Egyptian King Soforon (or Safron).
Saint Mary heals a woman possessed by evil spirits.
Saint Mary turns water over which her anaphora was recited by Abba Samuˀel of Wali into miraculous bread.
The story of Dilasor, brother of Emperor Theodosius, who was Abba Kiros.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Christ orders Abba Samu'el of Wali to celebrate Mass for the feast of Saint Mary.
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Abba Samuˀel of Wali is lifted up while reciting the Wəddase Maryam.
Oz, the Byzantine monk, is shown a vision of Hell by Saint Urael.
The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.
column23: According to the catalog, the manuscript folios are rebound in disorder. The correct order is 16r-49v, 58r-65v, 50r-57v, 66r-137v. The miracle numbers are assigned based on this (corrected) order. Catalog: https://archive.org/details/EMMLCatalog09/page/n31/mode/2up/search/3536.

column4: The repentant knight who could pray only the Hail Mary.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
The bishop for whom Saint Mary tailored a new sackcloth sends a penitent to Santiago.
The deacon's prayer that contained five times "Rejoice!" [tafassehiyat].
The pilgrim to Santiago whom Satan persuaded to mutilate himself after falling into a sexual sin.
The priest who could only say the Mass of the Virgin Mary.
The knight who wanted to seduce the daughter of the cobbler.
The Jewish boy who received Holy Communion with his Christian companions.
A man who drowned when a pilgrim ship sank is resuscitated.
The divorced wife who prayed for revenge against her rival.
The woman from Rome whose daughter rose up on the anniversary of her death.
The widow who prayed to Saint Mary and saved her only son from death by hanging.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
The sister of Emperor Constantine who prayed to know how Saint Mary bore the Word of God, but then failed to recognize her Son when he appeared to her in church.
The young novice whom Saint Mary encouraged to persevere in his vocation.
The pious official who was accused of embezzlement and of having an affair with the wife of his lord.
The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
A nun sacristan elopes with a priest, but afterwards they repent.
The sinful woman who despaired when she kept on sinning and swallowed a scorpion.
column23: According to the catalog, miracle number 24.[!]. Catalog: https://archive.org/details/EMMLCatalog09/page/n31/mode/2up.

column4: The bee keeper who consulted a sorceress to have more honey.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
A nun in prison for her faith prays for two virgins.
The prudent monk who suspected that the food that the monks were eating was harmful, but then saw Saint Mary making it tasty for them.
The woman who was prevented from fasting by her husband.
The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
The rich merchant from Constantinople who lost all his money and made the icon of Saint Mary his guarantor when he borrowed money from a usurer.
column23: The miracle continues on f. 50r (according to Macomber handlist)

column4: Saint Mary saves from a lion a pious monk who had drunk too much wine.
The two brothers from Rome, Peter, a deacon, and Stephen, an avaricious magistrate.
The husband who broke his vow that he would live celibately with his wife.
The merchant who distributed as alms the money that had been loaned him by a friend.
column23: also on 57v, 66r (catalog)

column4: Saint Mary saves the soul of a rich sinner who had repented and was planning to build a monastery and become a monk.
Pachomius, the avaricious patriarch of Rome, who sold the chrism of the church.
The avaricious priest who visited a dying man who loved bribes.
The nun who was dissuaded from eloping with a knight by a vision of Hell.
The shepherd near the church of Saint Paul in Rome who was possessed by a demon.
The monk who has carried by the bretheren to church when he became too sick to walk.
The rich knight who was advised by an abbot to pray to Saint Mary to win the heart of the woman with whom he was in love.
The monk custodian of the church who prayed to see Saint Mary.
column23: with a question mark (catalog)

column4: The bankrupt merchant to whom Satan offered two pearls if he would deny Christ and Saint Mary.
A herdsman saves his beasts in a storm by praying to Saint Mary.
The pious mower of hay to whom the gatekeeper gave his daughter in marriage.
The rich woman who went with the monks to the manbalis for prayer and there saw a vision of Saint Mary.
The robber whom a bishop was commanded to bury after he was executed.
The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
The Jewish cowherd who was baptized by his Christian companions.
The mighty Goliath threatens to destroy the monastery of Saint Mary.
The Muslim who found an icon of Saint Mary in his house.
The only son of a king who dedicated himself to Saint Mary.
The young man who was ready to serve Satan, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
A knight tries to seduce the wife of a friend, but she is saved by a vision.
The pious rich man whom Satan served in hopes of destroying him.
The peasant who became rich from other people's goods.
The hypocritical superior of a monastery who pretended to be religious.
The Jew of Constantinople who threw an icon of Saint Mary into the latrine.
The woman from Rome who killed the baby she bore after sleeping with her son
The monk who got himself appointed abbot of another monastery by the king, without the consent of the monks.
The young man who offered the ring he had received from his girlfriend to the icon of Saint Mary.
A ship that was about to founder is saved when they pray to Saint Mary.
The Jew who attacked the icon of Saint Mary when he failed to obtain by litigation someone else's property.
The knight who denied Christ at the bidding of Satan, in order to have fine clothes for a reception, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
The monk who was custodian of a church near a river and drowned while trying to cross to visit his lover.
The nun who used to pray for the dead, but lost her virginity and died before completing her penance.
The nun whom Saint Mary admonished to recite the Hail Mary more attentively.
Saint Basil cycle: The proud men who wanted to have a splendid icon of Saint Mary made.
The virgin who sinned with many lovers.
The stone-footed man (i. e., a man with gout) from France.

column15: ወሀለዉ፡ አኃው፡ ፪፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፡ ለአሐዱ፡ ስሙ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወለካልኡ፡ እስጢፋኖስ፡ ወጴጥሮስ፡ ዲያቆን፡ ውእቱ፡ ለቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን

column4: Saint Mary saves the soul of a rich sinner who had repented and was planning to build a monastery and become a monk.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ፈረሳዊ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ማልኮስ፡ ዘሀገረ፡ ንሒሳ፡ ወክቡር፡ ውእቱ፡ ወባዕል፡ ጥቀ፡ ወብዙኅ፡ ንዋዩ፡ ወገራውኢሁ፡ እስመ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወጊጉይ፡ ውእቱ፡ ፈረሳዊ፡ ማልኮስ፡ ወኢይዜከሮ፡ ለሞት

column4: Pachomius, the avaricious patriarch of Rome, who sold the chrism of the church.
column15: ወነበረ፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዲበ፡ መንበረ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ፓኵሚስ፡ እስመ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ ንዋይ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወይነሥእ፡ ንዋየ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ለመፍቅዱ፡ ወለጻሕቁ፡ ወእምብዝኃ፡ ድፍረቱ፡ ነሥአ፡ ሜሮነ፡ እምቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወሤጦ፡ ለንዋይ

column4: The avaricious priest who visited a dying man who loved bribes.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ እምብሔረ፡ ግብጽ፡ ዘያፈቅር፡ ንዋየ። ወሀሎ፡ ካዕበ፡ ካልእ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘያፈቅር፡ ሕልያነ፡ ሐመ፡ ዐቢየ፡ ሕማመ

column4: The nun who was dissuaded from eloping with a knight by a vision of Hell.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ይነብር፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ዘስማ፡ ደብረ፡ ምጥማቅ፡ ወትነብር፡ ውስተ፡ ይእቲ፡ ደብር፡ አሐቲ፡ መበለት፡ ንእስት፡ ዘሠናይ፡ ሥነ፡ ላሕያ። ወኮነት፡ ይእቲ፡ መበለት፡ ታፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ መዝገበ፡ ምሕረት፡ ወሣህል፡ ወትትፌሣሕ፡ በበዐላቲሃ፡ ለለኵሉ፡ አውራኅ፡ ወታስተፌሥሖሙ፡ ለነዳያን፡ ወለምስኪናን። ወሶበ፡ ርእየ፡ ሰይጣን፡ ግዕዛ፡ ሠናየ፡ ቀንዓ፡ ላዕሌሃ፡ ወቦአ፡ ውስተ፡ ልበ፡ አሐዱ፡ ፈረሳዊ

column4: The shepherd near the church of Saint Paul in Rome who was possessed by a demon.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፡ አመ፡ መዋዕለ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ሳባ፡ ፈተዉ፡ ውሑዳን፡ ሰብእ፡ ይሖሩ፡ ኀበ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያና፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ከመ፡ ይግነዩ፡ ወይስግዱ፡ ውስቴታ። ወእንዘ፡ የሐውሩ፡ በፍኖት፡ ሃደሩ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘተሐንጸት፡ በስመ፡ ሐዋርያ፡ ጳውሎስ

column4: The monk who has carried by the bretheren to church when he became too sick to walk.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ማእከለ፡ ባሕረ፡ ጤግሮስ፡ ደሴት፡ ዘይሰመይ፡ ደብረ፡ ኤፍሬም፡ ወይነብሩ፡ ውስቴታ፡ ብዙኃን፡ መነኮሳት፡ ወእም፡ ውስቴቶሙ፡ ሀሎ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘመንኰሰ፡ እምንእሱ፡ ወይትለአክ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ በሠናይ፡ አምልኮ፡ በፍቅረ፡ ዚአሃ

column4: The rich knight who was advised by an abbot to pray to Saint Mary to win the heart of the woman with whom he was in love.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ፈረሳዊ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ኒፎን፡ ዘሀገረ፡ ገለአድ፡ ዝሁር፡ ውእቱ፡ ወሬዛ፡ ወይትሜካሕ፡ በብዙኅ፡ ብዕሉ፡ ወይሰረገው፡ በአልባሰ፡ ወርቅ፡ ወይትአጸፍ፡ ሜላተ። ወአሐተ፡ ዕለተ፡ እንዘ፡ ያንሶሱ፡ ማእከለ፡ ምሥያጣት፡ ወውስተ፡ መራኅብት፡ ነጸረ፡ ለአሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ በዐይነ፡ ፍትወት

column4: The monk custodian of the church who prayed to see Saint Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ናታን፡ በደብረ፡ ሰራብዮን፡ ኀበ፡ መነኮሳት፡ ዘይእቲ፡ ደብር፡ ወውእቱ፡ መጋቢ፡ ዘየዐቅብ፡ መዛግብተ፡ ዘቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወውእቱ፡ ዘይጠቅዕ፡ መጥቅዓ፡ በጊዜ፡ ጸሎት፡ ዘሰዓታት

column4: The bankrupt merchant to whom Satan offered two pearls if he would deny Christ and Saint Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ነጋዲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ጥብርያኖስ፡ በሀገረ፡ ቅፍጥ፡ እስመ፡ ባዕል፡ ጥቀ፡ በአግብርት፡ ወበአእማት፡ በወርቅ፡ ወበብሩር፡ ወአልሕምት፡ ወአግማል፡ ወዘይነግድ፡ ዲበ፡ የብስ፡ ወባሕር ። ወተወለጠ፡ ላዕሌሁ፡ መዋዕል፡ ወአዝማን፡ ወኃልቀ፡ ኵሉ፡ ንዋዩ

column4: A herdsman saves his beasts in a storm by praying to Saint Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ኖላዊ፡ ዘይሬኢ፡ አልህምተ፡ ወእንስሳ፡ ወኮነ፡ ብእሲ፡ የዋህ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. በልቡ፡ ወኮነ፡ ይትለአክ፡ ወይቀውም፡ ቅድሜሃ፡ ውስተ፡ ኵሉ፡ መካን፡ ወኢያጸርዕ፡ ሰላመ፡ መልአክ፡ ዛቲ፡ ወኮነ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ሰላም፡ ውስተ፡ አፉሁ፡ መዐልተ፡ ወሌሊተ፡ በሑረቱ፡ ወበግብአቱ፡ በንብረቱ፡ ወበተንሥኦቱ። ወአመ፡ በዐላ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ተንሥአ፡ አውሎ፡ ወበረድ፡ በይእቲ፡ ሌሊት፡ ወሐለየ፡ ውእቱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ከመ፡ ይመውቱ፡ እንስሳሁ፡ በይእቲ፡ ሌሊት

column4: The pious mower of hay to whom the gatekeeper gave his daughter in marriage.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ወሬዛ፡ ዘይነብር፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ወሠናይ፡ ውእቱ፡ እምወራዙት፡ ወኄር፡ በፍኖቱ፡ ወንጹሕ፡ ወጽሩይ፡ ወፈራሄ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘያፈቅር፡ ሠናያተ፡ ወይጸልእ፡ እኩያተ፡ እምንእሱ። ወነዳይ፡ ውእቱ፡ ይበልዕ፡ እምፍሬ፡ ጻማሁ፡ ወኮነ፡ ኵሎ፡ ዕለተ፡ የሐውር፡ ውስተ፡ ገዳም፡ ወይሴጽር፡ ዕፀወ፡ አው፡ የዓጽድ፡ ሣዕረ፡ ወይሠይጦ፡ ውስተ፡ ምሥያት

column4: The rich woman who went with the monks to the manbalis for prayer and there saw a vision of Saint Mary.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ሶበ፡ ፈቀዱ፡ አኃው፡ ከመ፡ ይትጋብኡ፡ ውስተ፡ መንበሊስ፡ ተንሥኡ፡ እምአብርፊስ፡ ኀበ፡ መንበሊስ፡ ወሖረት፡ ምስሌሆሙ፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ዐባይ፡ ወክብርት

column4: The robber whom a bishop was commanded to bury after he was executed.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ሠራቂ፡ ዘይሴሰይ፡ በሠሪቅ፡ ወባሕቱ፡ ይሁብ፡ ሰላማ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…፡ ብዙኃ፡ ጊዜያት፡ በልብ፡ ንጹሕ፡ ወበትሕትና፡ ወበየውሃት፡ ወሶበ፡ ኮነ፡ ይዜክር፡ ስማ፡ ይትሀወክ፡ እስመ፡ ፍቅራ፡ ውስተ፡ ልቡ

column4: The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ገባራዊ፡ ዘኮነ፡ ያወትር፡ ኵሎ፡ ዕለተ፡ ሰላማ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ሰርከ፡ ወነግሃ፡ ወመንፈቀ፡ መዓልት፡ ወነበረ፡ ከመዝ፡ ብዙኃ፡ መዋዕለ። ወአሐተ፡ ዕለተ፡ ይቤላ፡ ኦእግዝእትየ፡ መስተሣህልት፡ እስመ፡ አንሰ፡ ወትረ፡ ከመዝ፡ እሁብ፡ ሰላመኪ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ኃፍረት፡ ወአንቲኒ፡ ለምንት፡ ዘኢታገብኢ፡ ሊተ፡ ሰላምየ

column4: The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፡ ዘተረፈ፡ አሐዱ፡ ወሬዛ፡ እምመዋዕለ፡ ተንበላት፡ ወተንበላታይ፡ ውእቱ። ወኮነ፡ ይበውእ፡ ኀበ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወይቀውም፡ ቅድሜ፡ ሥዕላ፡ ለእግዝእትነ
column23: Catalog gives f 80r and miracle number 89 for ID 163 (https://archive.org/details/EMMLCatalog09/page/n201/mode/2up). Macomber gives f 79 v for the long form of ID 163, and it is on f 79v. Ms: https://www.vhmml.org/readingRoom/view/205677. I think Macomber is right: there are two miracles on f 79v, no miracle starts on f 80r. If so, correct the miracle numbers (they are taken from the catalog).

column4: The Jewish cowherd who was baptized by his Christian companions.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አይሁዳዊ፡ ዘቦቱ፡ መራዕየ፡ አልህምት፡ ወቦቱ፡ አሐዱ፡ ወልደ፡ ዘይሬኢ፡ አልህምተ፡ አቡሁ፡ አፍአ፡ እምሀገር፡ ምስለ፡ ደቂቀ፡ ክርስቲያን። ወበአሐቲ፡ እምመዋዕል፡ ተጋብኡ፡ እሉ፡ ኖሎት፡ ከመ፡ ይብልዑ፡ ኅብስተ

column4: The mighty Goliath threatens to destroy the monastery of Saint Mary.

column15: ስምዑኬ፡ አበውየ፡ ወአኃውየ፡ ዘንተ፡ ተአምረ፡ ዘገብረት፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. በውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ መካን፡ በዕለተ፡ በዓላ። ጸሎታ፡…. ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ውስተ፡ ውእቱ፡ መካን፡ ዘይእኅዝ፡ መራኁተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን

column4: Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The life of Saint Mary to the birth of Christ.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ወነገረቶ፡ ሑረያቲሁ፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡ ወምስለ፡ ዮሴፍ፡ ወምስለ፡ ሰሎሜ። ጸሎታ፡…. ይቤ፡ ጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ አንሰ፡ ርኢክዋ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ናሁ፡ ወረደት፡ እምሰማይ

column4: Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The flight into Egypt.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ወተናገረቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት። ጸሎታ፡…. ወናሁ፡ አስተርአዮ፡ ገብርኤል፡ መልአክ፡ ለዮሴፍ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ተንሥእ፡ ወንሣእ፡ ሕፃነ፡ ወእሞ፡ ወሑር፡ እምድረ፡ ግብጽ

column4: Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family receives hospitality from a shepherd.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ወተናገረቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት። ጸሎታ፡…. ወሶበ፡ ዐደውነ፡ ወኃለፍናሃ፡ ለእንትኩ፡ መከራት፡ ኵላ፡ ዘውስተ፡ እንታክቲ፡ ፍናዊት

column4: Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family crosses the Nile at Asmunayn.
Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Christ Child grants Saint Mary a vision of his future glory.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ወተናገረቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት። ጸሎታ፡…. ወይቤለኒ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልድየ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ኦወለዲትየ፡ ርእዪ፡ ኀበ፡ መትሕት

column4: Saint Mary gives a thirsty dog water to drink from her shoe.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተየቶ፡ ለከልብ፡ ጽሙእ፡ በአሣዕና። ጸሎታ፡…. ወሀለወት፡ አንስት፡ ምስለ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ወመጽአ፡ ከልብ፡ ወሰደዳሁ፡ ውእቶን፡ አንስት

column4: Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): Ahrufas, the guardian angel of Egypt, comes to the Holy Family.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ወተናገረቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት። ጸሎታ፡…. ወመጽአ፡ ኀቤነ፡ አኅሩፋስ፡ መልአክ፡ ዘየዓቅባለ፡ ምድረ፡ ግብጽ፡ ወሰገደ፡ ለፍቁር፡ ወልድየ፡ ከመ፡ ሕዙን

column4: Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The experience of the Holy Family in the district of Asmunayn.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ወተናገረቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት። ጸሎታ፡…. ወኮነ፡ ብነ፡ ውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ አስሞኒን፡ እምድንጋፄ፡ ወፍርሃት፡ ወሐዘን

column4: Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family encounters thieves.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ወተናገረቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት። ጸሎታ፡…. ወኮነ፡ እምድኅረ፡ በአትነ፡ እምዝንቱ፡ መካን፡ ፍርሃት፡ ብዙኅ። ወወፅኡ፡ ላዕሌነ፡ ፈያት፡ ወአፍርሁነ፡ ጥቀ

column4: Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family arrives at Däbrä QWesqWam.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ወተናገረቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት። ጸሎታ፡…. ወሶበ፡ በጻሕነ፡ ኀቤሁ፡ ናንሶሱ፡ ዝየ፡ ወዝየ፡ ዮጊ፡ ለእመ፡ ንረክብ፡ መካነ፡ ሠናየ፡ ከመ፡ ንንበር፡ ውስቴቱ

column4: Saint Peter gives Saint John Chrysostom the keys of the kingdom and Saint John the Evangelist gives him the Gospels; then Saint Mary appears to him.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ለዮሐንስ፡ አፈ፡ ወርቅ፡ በአልባስ፡ ጸዓዳ፡ ከመ፡ ዘበረድ። ጸሎታ፡…. ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘሀገረ፡ ቍስጥንጥንያ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ አፈ፡ ወርቅ፡ ወእንዘ፡ ሀሎ፡ ውእቱ፡ እምቅድመ፡ ይንሣእ፡ ሢመተ፡ ቅስና

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: The Jews try to burn down the house where Saint Mary is staying but are burned up instead.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ወፅአት፡ እሳት፡ ወአውዓዮሙ፡ ለአይሁድ። ጸሎታ፡…. ወእምድኅረ፡ ኃምስ፡ መዋዕል፡ እንዘ፡ ሀለወት፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. በቤተ፡ ልሔም፡ አእመረ፡ መኰንን፡ ወሊቃነ፡ ካህናት፡ ከመ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤታ

column4: The Holy Spirit recounts the salvific events that have occurred on Sunday.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ተናገረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ክብራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ጸሎታ፡…. ወእምዝ፡ እምድኅረ፡ አስተርአየ፡ ዝተአምር፡ ላዕለ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ወላዕለ፡ አርድእት፡ ዘተናገረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወይቤ፡ አእምሩኬ፡ ከመ፡ በዕለተ፡ እሑድ፡ አብሰራ፡ ገብርኤል፡ መልአክ፡ ለማርያም፡ ቅድስት

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays with the disciples.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ጸለየት፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም። ጸሎታ፡…. ወጸለየት፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ወትቤ፡ እግዚእየ፡ ወአምላኪየ፡ ስፋሕ፡ እዴከ፡ ወባርክ፡ ላዕሌየ

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays with the disciples (continuation).
column15: ዘከመ፡ ጸለየት፡ ካዕበ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም። ጸሎታ፡…. ወካዕበ፡ ጸለየት፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ኦእግዚእየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልደ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ ዘይገብር፡ ኵሎ፡ ዘፈቀደ፡ በሰማይ፡ ወበምድር

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays for the release of the souls in judgment.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አውፅአት፡ ነፍሳተ፡ እለ፡ እምውስተ፡ ደይን። ጸሎታ፡…. እፈቅድኬ፡ ዮም፡ ከመ፡ ትፈጽም፡ ሊተ፡ ኀሢሦትየ፡ ወታዕርግ፡ ኵሎ፡ ነፍሳተ፡ ዘውስተ፡ ኵነኔ

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint John the Evangelist sees a vision of Saint Mary in glory.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ርእያ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ነጕድጓድ፡ በዕለተ፡ ፍልሰታ፡ በከመ፡ ተስእለ፡ በእንቲአሃ። ጸሎታ፡…. ወአንሰ፡ እቤ፡ ኦእግዚእየ፡ ውስተ፡ አይኑ፡ መካናት፡ ሀለወት፡ ወላዲትከ፡ ድንግል

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Christ celebrates Mass for Saint Mary.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ተክህነ፡ እግዚእነ፡ በዕለተ፡ ፍልሰታ፡ ለወላዲቱ፡ ዘከመ፡ አቅረቦሙ፡ ለአርድእቱ፡ ወለኵሉ፡ ጉባኤ። ጸሎታ፡…. ወእምድኅረ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ኮነ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ካህነ፡ ለሥጋ፡ ወላዲቱ፡ ቅድስት

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary asks Christ that the disciples preach her Transitus and Assumption.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ተስእለቶ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ለወልዳ፡ ከመ፡ ይስብኩ፡ ፍልሰታ፡ ወዕርገታ። ጸሎታ፡…. በሊ፡ ለአርድእት፡ ከመ፡ በዝንቱ፡ ይስብኩ፡ ቍርባነ፡ ዘዮም

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary asks that Saint John be allowed to visit her dwelling place.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ሰአለቶ፡ ለወልዳ፡ ከመ፡ ያምጽኦ፡ ለዮሐንስ፡ ወትርአዮ። ጸሎታ፡…. ወጸለየት፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ እንዘ፡ ትብል፡ ኦእግዚእየ፡ ወአምላኪየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘኀረያ፡ ለአመቱ፡ ድሉተ፡ ለተስብኦቱ

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Prochorus reports Saint John's visit to Saint Mary's dwelling place.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ርእየ፡ ማኅደራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ንጕድጓድ። ጸሎታ፡…. ወይቤለኒ፡ አቡየ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ሊተ፡ ለአብሮኮሮስ፡ ወለመስተጋብኣን፡ ሰላም፡ ለክሙ። ወኢኃደገ፡ እንዘ፡ ይምዕዶሙ፡ ለጉቡኣን፡ እስከ፡ ጌሰም

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays to be taken from this life.
column15: ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየ፡ ገብርኤል፡ መልአክ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም። ጸሎታ፡…. ወትቤ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ እንዘ፡ ሀለወት፡ በቤተ፡ ልሔም፡ ኦእግዚእየ፡ ሊቅ፡ ኄር፡ ፈኑ፡ ወንሥአኒ፡ እምዝዓለም፡ ዘምሉእ፡ ሐዘናት፡ ወሁከታት

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: The Jews go to Bethlehem to seize Saint Mary but are blinded.
column15: ዘከመ፡ ዖርያ፡ አዕይንቲሆሙ፡ ለአይሁድ፡  ወተጸለታ። ጸሎታ፡…. ወሶበ፡ ርእዩ፡ ተአምራተ፡ ወመንክራተ፡ ዘይገብር፡ ክርስቶስ፡ በቤተ፡ ልሔም፡ በእንተ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ወኵሎሙ፡ እለ፡ ቦሙ፡ ደዌ፡ ወሕማመ፡ ይመጽኡ፡ ኀበ፡ እግዝእትነ

column4: Mary, Assumption of cycle: Christ, together with Saint Mary and the angels, appears to the Apostles and asks them to build churches in his name and hers throughout the world.

column23: Evgeniia changed the canonical incipit for this story variation to EMML 6835 (26v) because Macomber gave incipits for two different versions of ID 164 from the same ms (EMML 3872). Since our ID extension is a ms name, we cannot distinguish the two versions even with ID extensions. The incipit of ID 164 in EMML 6835 (made the canonical incipit for this story variation) is very similar to the incipit of ID 164 in EMML 3872 (146r).
