Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil and the rich man who refused to give him a tablet [saleda] for an icon of Saint Mary.
Saint Mary heals a servant girl from a magic spell.
column15: ወከመ፡ ኆፀ፡ ባሕር፡ ኍላቋሁ፡ ከማሁ፡ ኢይትረከብ፡ ኍልቈ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ርኁቅ፡ ውእቱ፡ እምልበ፡ መዋቲ፡ ኢይትረከብ፡ በኃሢሥ፡ ወኢይትሌለይ፡ በጥንቃቄ፡ በልሳነ፡ መዋቲ፡ ነባቢ፡ ኢይክል፡ ፍጻሜሁ። ወይእዜኒ፡ እንግርክሙ፡ በከመ፡ ሰማዕኩ፡ ቀዲሙ፡ በዕዝንየ፡ ወከማሁ፡ ርኢኩ፡ በአዕይንትየ፡ ዘገብረት፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ተአምር፡ ወእዜኑ፡ ንስቲተ፡ እምተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. እንዘ፡ ያሌብወኒ፡ መንፈሰ፡ ወልዳ፡ ገባሬ፡ ዓለም፡ በጥበቢሁ፡ ሰጊድ፡ ይደሉ፡ ለስመ፡ ዚአሁ፡ ይእዜኒ፡ ወዘልፈኒ፡ ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ዓመት፡ በቤተ፡ አጋዕዝታ፡ ወሶበ፡ ሖሩ፡ አጋዕዝቲሃ፡ ኀዲጎሙ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤቶሙ፡ ወሠወረ፡ ሶቤሃ፡ ፀሐይ፡ ብርሃኖ

column4: Daniel from Constantinople, who wanted to go to church to receive Communion even when there was fighting in the streets.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ቍስጥንጥንየ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ዳንኤል፡ ዘይፈርሆ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘኵሎ፡ ይእኅዝ፡ በጸንዓ፡ ኃይሉ፡ ዘያርዕድ፡ ለሰማይ፡ ወያድለቅልቃ፡ ለምድር፡ በምጽአቱ

column4: The story of Julius Aqfahasi.
The story of King Tarses of Fars, who loved to kill Christians.
The Jew from Rome who wanted to kill Christians, but was seized by the priests of the church of Saint Mary.
Archbishop Tilas, who was seized by Jews while carrying a golden chalice.
Elias from Elkesus, who was falsely accused and was suspended by the abbot.
King Yasay of Egypt, who became a monk in Däbrä Rom.
A dragon that had swallowed up Efrem, a monk of Däbrä Timona, is compelled to vomit him up alive ten days later.
Saint Mary heals the wounds of Ermeyis of Sidon with a drop of her milk.
Patriarch Tewoqritos of Jerusalem rebukes King Akratis of Egypt for not fasting or praying.
Deganna, the church builder, who was asked by King Aktab to build a temple for his pagan gods.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ሳም፡ ዘስሙ፡ ዴገና፡ ሐናፄ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘይጸርብ፡ ዕፀወ፡ ወይወቅር፡ ዕብነ

column4: Sara from Mesot, who became insane and went about naked.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ በሀገረ፡ ምሶት፡ ዘስማ፡ ሳራ፡ ዘታፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወባቲ፡ ደዌ፡ ዕፁበ፡ ወአኃዛ፡ ለዘኳንና፡ ነገርጓር

column4: The story of Astaqaˀos, the European potter who was buried alive.
King Bartaqu of Greece, who became a monk.
Barnabas from Sandafa, who used to venerate Saint Mary's icon.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ሰንደፋ፡ ዘስሙ፡ በርናባስ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ ጸሎት፡ ወጾም፡ ወገያሴ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘኮነ፡ ያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወይተግህ፡ መዓልተ፡ ወሌሊተ፡ እንበለ፡ አጽርዖ፡ አንብቦ፡ ውዳሴሃ

column4: Thecla cycle: Saint Mary incenses Thecla (continuation).
Vision of Gregory the Seer [ra'eya hebu'at].
The story of Awr, the son of the princess and the magician, Abrasit.
Paraleya from Iyyoram, who was beaten by her husband because she was childless.
Qawestos, the husband of Akroseya, becomes a disciple of Saint Clement.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ መኰንን፡ በሀገረ፡ ቃህራ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወይትቀነይ፡ ላቲ፡ ወይገብር፡ በዓለ፡ ፍልሰተ፡ ዚአሃ፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ሰናይት፡ ወፈራሂተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወትከብር፡ በዓላ፡ ወሰንበታተ፡ ቦሙ፡ ፪፡ ውሉድ፡ እምድኅረ፡ ኮኑ፡ መካን፡ ዘወሀበቶሙ፡ እግዝእትነ

column4: The story of Saint Menas and his brother.
The temptations that Akroseya, the wife of Qawestos, overcame.
When Pariqos of Fesa confesses his sins to the bishop, the latter, refusing him absolution, tells him to go to Abba Yaceqob (Santiago).
The conversion of a Muslim merchant who had been imprisoned in Naples.
The magistrate whom the king accused of embezzlement.
The hunter who caught a gassa kalb in his net.
Saint Mary appears to a priest of Däbrä Maryam in Sire.
Saint Alexius lives for fifteen years near a church of Saint Mary in Armenia.
Holy Family journey cycle: The hunter who discovered the Holy Family in flight is turned into a dog when he violates his oath not to reveal them.
The thieves who stole the furnishings of a church of Saint Mary and refused to restore them when she appeared to them.
The new tabot of Saint Mary that was found outside the box in which it had been placed.
The Ethiopian general who went off to fight the Muslims without the consent of the king.
The punishment of an Ethiopian woman who swore falsely that she had not committed adultery with another woman's husband.
Zärˀa Yaˁəqob miracles: Zärˀa Yaˁəqob and Batergela Maryam, who is accused of treason and is imprisoned but delivered from the plague.
Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family arrives at Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam.
Däbrä Metmaq miracles: The Muslims who spent the night at the ruins of Däbrä Metmaq.
Däbrä Metmaq miracles: Mary punishes the untrustworthy camel driver of Däbrä Metmaq who steals from it.
The rich persons who stored their wealth in a church.
A Christian community is attacked by a neighboring Muslim community.
A Jew is led to baptism by a dream about a lion and a monk; afterwards he curses a Jew at the latter's request.
A monk, while guarding a church, has a nocturnal emission and finds himself suddenly outside the courtyard of the church.
The blind teacher whom his pupils wanted to push over a cliff while they were on their way to a feast being given in honor of the Assumption.
When a couple tries to marry their son whom they had dedicated to Saint Mary, he falls sick to the point of death.
King Dawit miracles: The monasteries summon King (Dawit) of Ethiopia to abdicate.
The pious monk who drowned while crossing a river on his way to a feast that was being given by a rich man in honor of the Assumption.
Thieves try to steal from a church of Saint Mary in Syria but are unable to bring what they have stolen out of the church.
The brother of Emperor Constantine who wanted to marry the empress while Constantine was on pilgrimage to Jerusalem.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ቍስጠንጢኖስ፡ ወስመ፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ብራቲላ፡ ወታፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወተካየደ፡ ውእቱ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ምስለ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ከመ፡ ይሑር፡ ኢየሩሳሌም፡ ኀበ፡ ተሰቅለ

column4: Homily on the miracles of Saint Mary.
Homily on the Annunciation and the Incarnation (opening)
column15: በእንተ፡ ስብከተ፡ ጌና፡ ወበእንተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወኤልሳቤጥ፡ ወበእንተ፡ ወልደ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዝውእቱ፡ ቃል፡ ዘኢይትነገር። ሀበኒ፡ ቃለ፡ ዘይዜምር፡ ስብሐቲከ፡ ባዕል፡ ኅቡዕ፡ ዘሠምረ፡ ይትከሠት

column4: Homily on the Annunciation and the Incarnation (continuation): The Miraculous Conception of Saint John the Baptist.
column15: ወናሁ፡ ኤልሳቤጥኒ፡ ፀንሰት፡ እንዘ፡ መካን፡ ይእቲ፡ እስመ፡ መንክር፡ ይእቲ፡ በመንክር፡ ተወክፈቶ

column4: Homily on the Annunciation and the Incarnation (continuation): The Visitation of Saint Mary to St. Elizabeth.
column15: ወሖረት፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ትርአየ፡ ለዓረጊት፡ ወእንተ፡ በልየት፡ ፀንሰት፡ እስመ፡ አምነት፡ ቃለ፡ ዘሰምዓት

column4: Homily on the Annunciation and the Incarnation (continuation): Gabriel the Archangel.
column15: ወፈነወ፡ በአፈ፡ ገብርኤል፡ መልአክ፡ ኀበ፡ ወለተ፡ ዳዊት፡ ወተምህረት፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ምስጢረ፡ ኅቡዓ፡ ባሕቲታ፡ ወከሠተት፡ ለሰብእ፡ ዘታነገራ፡ መልአክ

column4: Homily on the Annunciation and the Incarnation (continuation): Holy Spirit.
column15: ወኤልሳቤጥኒ፡ እንዘ፡ ዓዲ፡ እስመ፡ ምልዕተ፡ መንፈስ፡ ይእቲ፡ አዕመረት፡ አንፈርዕፆቶ፡ ለሕፃን፡ ወቀፀበቶ፡ ለአቡሁ

column4: Homily on the Annunciation and the Incarnation (continuation): Home of Saint Mary
column15: ወተመይጠት፡ ትግባዕ፡ ኀበ፡ ቤተ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ወእምድኅረ፡ ዝንቱ፡ እስመ፡ በጽሐ፡ ጊዜሃ፡ ትለድ፡ ወሌዋዊ፡ ዮሴፍ፡ ተወክፈ፡ ወአዕመረ፡ ከመ፡ ፀንሰት፡ እግዝእትነ

column4: Homily on the Annunciation and the Incarnation (continuation): Mysteries.
column15: ምስጢር፡ ኅቡዕ፡ ዘተነግረ፡ እምኀበ፡ አብ፡ አምላክከ፡ ይዕቀብዎ፡ ከመ፡ ኢትክሥቱ፡ ለዘአፍአ

column4: Saint Mary appears to Saint Theodore the Anatolian.
Emperor Honorius, who lived like a monk.
A column falls and breaks the leg of the son of an official when Muslims destroy a church of Saint Mary in Homs.
The prodigal son of a man who used, when he was alive, to feed two persons; Saint Mary promises him riches, but he finds only two grains of gold.
The monk who was expelled from school when he could not pay his teacher.
The mourning of Saint John the Baptist for his mother.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ መጥምቅ፡ እንዘ፡ ገዳመ፡ አጐየየቶ፡ እሙ፡ ኤልሳቤጥ፡ ውስተ፡ ገዳም፡ አመ፡ ቀተሎሙ፡ ሄሮድስ፡ ለሕፃናት

column4: Saint Mary appears to the gabaz of her church in Waybela and tells him about the fall of Badlay.
The chastisement of the heretic, Nestorius.
Mary, Assummption of: In a vision Saint Mary is shown the Paradise of the Just.
column15: ወትቤ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ወአውሥአኒ፡ ወይቤለኒ፡ ወልድየ፡ ንዒ፡ ኀቤየ፡ ኦእምየ፡ ናንሶሱ፡ ኀበ፡ ገነተ፡ ጻድቃን

column4: Saint Mary's promises to those who are devoted to her.
column15: ስምዑ፡ እንግርክሙ፡ ውሉደ፡ ጥምቀት፡ ዘትቤ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ዕድ፡ ወአንስት፡ አዕሩግ፡ ወሕፃናት፡ ቀሳውስት፡ ወዲያቆናት፡ እለ፡ ትቀውሙ፡ ዝየ፡ ለሰሚዓ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ክቡር፡ ወልዑል፡ ወሥሙር፡ ወታስምዐነ፡ ቃለ፡ ፍሥሐ፡ ወሐሴት፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን። ወትቤ፡ ለኒ፡ በዝዓለም፡ አዓቅበክሙ፡ እምዕለት፡ እኪት፡ ወእምሰዓታተ፡ መንሱት

column4: A Roman official is prevented from approaching the Holy Sepulcher.
The Egyptian woman who lost a silver plate while bathing in a miraculous spring.
The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
Maryam from Dǝfrā, a child who wanted to receive Communion but was shut up in the house when her family went to church, goes to heaven.
The French artist who fell from the scaffolding while painting frescoes.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
Saint Mary carries a dying monk to Jerusalem.
The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
Three Arabs, journeying to Rif on the Nile in Egypt, fall into the water due to a storm and two are saved from crocodiles.
The rich man from Colosse who was shot in the eye with an arrow while fighting the Qwez.
The church of Saint Mary that moved by itself to the shore of the Mediterranean Sea.
The story of the blind priest, Yohannes Bakansi; Mary heals his eyes with milk from her breasts
Elizabeth, the blind daughter of Abraham and Gera Anest of Baderman.
The widow who could not find husbands for her three daughters.
The two brothers who copied the Miracles of Mary and fell into the doing of a sin.
Saint Mary appears to the martyr, Giyorgis Haddis, in prison.
Katir, the old priest from Elkesus, who was about to be dismissed from the church.
The story of the two brothers from Dalga who were dyers.
The stone-footed man (i. e., a man with gout) from France.
Bishop Mercurius, whom the patriarch wanted to remove because of leprosy.
A poor woman with a broken leg is healed by the icon of Saint Mary in the church of Harat ar-Rum.
The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
The deacon's prayer that contained five times "Rejoice!" [tafassehiyat].
Dabra Qaləmon miracles: The monk of Dabra Qaləmon who humbly pretends not to fast and is saved from his brothers by Mary.
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The widow who prayed to Saint Mary and saved her only son from death by hanging.
The pregnant woman who was caught by the tide while going to the church of Saint Michael (Mont Saint Michel)
The rich man who threw dry bread to a beggar in the name of Saint Mary.
The daughter of the rich man from Caesarea who could not deliver her baby.
The virgin who sinned with many lovers.
The faded icon of Saint Mary that the mother-in-law wanted to discard.
The sinful deacon who was healed by a drop of Saint Mary's milk.
The woman from Cairo whose nine children all died; Mary helped her conceive three more.
The thief whom the king's soldiers could not kill.
Saint Mary commands a deacon to give Christian burial to a sinful deacon assassinated by his enemies; when they disinter him, a flower is found in his mouth.
The bishop for whom Saint Mary tailored a new sackcloth sends a penitent to Santiago.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
The priest who could only say the Mass of the Virgin Mary.
Alexander, a Jew from Jerusalem, is delivered three days after he was swallowed up by a dragon.
The pious official who was accused of embezzlement and of having an affair with the wife of his lord.
The rich woman who went with the monks to the manbalis for prayer and there saw a vision of Saint Mary.
The Muslim who found an icon of Saint Mary in his house.

column15: ወበይእቲ፡ ዕለት፡ ብዙኃ፡ ፍቅር፡ ወኃይል፡ ወምሕረት፡ ወብዕል፡ ጸጋሁ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘመንገለ፡ ሰብእ

column4: Mary, Annunciation of cycle: Homily on the Annunciation, preceded by the gospel text.
column15: ወበሳድስ፡ ወርኅ፡ ተፈነወ፡ ገብርኤል፡ መልአክ፡ እምኀበ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ሀገረ፡ ገሊላ፡…. እንዘ፡ ኢየአምር፡ ብእሴ። ኦቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ እንተ፡ አውሥአቶ፡ ለመልአክ፡ በግህደት፡ ንጽሕት፡ ድንግልናሃ

column4: Mary, Annunciation of cycle: The Annunciation.
column15: ኀደረ፡ እግዚእ፡ ውስተ፡ ከርሠ፡ ድንግል፡ ፱፡ አውራኃ፡ ወ፭፡ ዕለተ፡ ከመ፡ ሰብእ፡ ልህቀ፡ ውስተ፡ ማኅፀን

column4: The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.
The sinful deacon who was healed by a drop of Saint Mary's milk.
The thief whom the king's soldiers could not kill.
The Emperor of Rome who erected an altar in his palace.
Saint Mary commands a deacon to give Christian burial to a sinful deacon assassinated by his enemies; when they disinter him, a flower is found in his mouth.
The repentant knight who could pray only the Hail Mary.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
The bishop for whom Saint Mary tailored a new sackcloth sends a penitent to Santiago.
The deacon's prayer that contained five times "Rejoice!" [tafassehiyat].
The pilgrim to Santiago whom Satan persuaded to mutilate himself after falling into a sexual sin.
The priest who could only say the Mass of the Virgin Mary.
The knight who wanted to seduce the daughter of the cobbler.
The Jewish boy who received Holy Communion with his Christian companions.
The pregnant woman who was caught by the tide while going to the church of Saint Michael (Mont Saint Michel)
The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
A man who drowned when a pilgrim ship sank is resuscitated.
The divorced wife who prayed for revenge against her rival.
The woman from Rome whose daughter rose up on the anniversary of her death.
The widow who prayed to Saint Mary and saved her only son from death by hanging.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
The sister of Emperor Constantine who prayed to know how Saint Mary bore the Word of God, but then failed to recognize her Son when he appeared to her in church.
The young novice whom Saint Mary encouraged to persevere in his vocation.
The pious official who was accused of embezzlement and of having an affair with the wife of his lord.
The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
A nun sacristan elopes with a priest, but afterwards they repent.
The bee keeper who consulted a sorceress to have more honey.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
A nun in prison for her faith prays for two virgins.
The sinful woman who despaired when she kept on sinning and swallowed a scorpion.
The prudent monk who suspected that the food that the monks were eating was harmful, but then saw Saint Mary making it tasty for them.
The woman who was prevented from fasting by her husband.
The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
The rich merchant from Constantinople who lost all his money and made the icon of Saint Mary his guarantor when he borrowed money from a usurer.
Saint Mary saves from a lion a pious monk who had drunk too much wine.
The husband who broke his vow that he would live celibately with his wife.
The merchant who distributed as alms the money that had been loaned him by a friend.
The two brothers from Rome, Peter, a deacon, and Stephen, an avaricious magistrate.
Saint Mary saves the soul of a rich sinner who had repented and was planning to build a monastery and become a monk.
Pachomius, the avaricious patriarch of Rome, who sold the chrism of the church.
The avaricious priest who visited a dying man who loved bribes.
The nun who was dissuaded from eloping with a knight by a vision of Hell.
The shepherd near the church of Saint Paul in Rome who was possessed by a demon.
The monk who has carried by the bretheren to church when he became too sick to walk.
The rich knight who was advised by an abbot to pray to Saint Mary to win the heart of the woman with whom he was in love.
The monk custodian of the church who prayed to see Saint Mary.
The bankrupt merchant to whom Satan offered two pearls if he would deny Christ and Saint Mary.
A herdsman saves his beasts in a storm by praying to Saint Mary.
The pious mower of hay to whom the gatekeeper gave his daughter in marriage.
The rich woman who went with the monks to the manbalis for prayer and there saw a vision of Saint Mary.
The robber whom a bishop was commanded to bury after he was executed.
The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
The Jewish cowherd who was baptized by his Christian companions.
The mighty Goliath threatens to destroy the monastery of Saint Mary.
The Muslim who found an icon of Saint Mary in his house.
The only son of a king who dedicated himself to Saint Mary.
The young man who was ready to serve Satan, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
A knight tries to seduce the wife of a friend, but she is saved by a vision.
The pious rich man whom Satan served in hopes of destroying him.
The peasant who became rich from other people's goods.
The hypocritical superior of a monastery who pretended to be religious.
The Jew of Constantinople who threw an icon of Saint Mary into the latrine.
The woman from Rome who killed the baby she bore after sleeping with her son
The monk who got himself appointed abbot of another monastery by the king, without the consent of the monks.
The young man who offered the ring he had received from his girlfriend to the icon of Saint Mary.
A ship that was about to founder is saved when they pray to Saint Mary.
The Jew who attacked the icon of Saint Mary when he failed to obtain by litigation someone else's property.
The knight who denied Christ at the bidding of Satan, in order to have fine clothes for a reception, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
The monk who was custodian of a church near a river and drowned while trying to cross to visit his lover.
The nun who used to pray for the dead, but lost her virginity and died before completing her penance.
The nun whom Saint Mary admonished to recite the Hail Mary more attentively.
Saint Basil cycle: The proud men who wanted to have a splendid icon of Saint Mary made.
The virgin who sinned with many lovers.
The stone-footed man (i. e., a man with gout) from France.
The man who was possessed by a spirit of epilepsy [nagargar] for 47 years.
The daughter of the chief of the thieves is cured of her leprosy at the miraculous spring.
Saint Mary saves the soul of a thief who was slain by the miraculous spring.
The brigands who killed each other at the miraculous spring.
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The rich man who threw dry bread to a beggar in the name of Saint Mary.
Vision of Theophilus of Alexandria (opening)
column15: በእንተ፡ ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ለቴዎፍሎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ወዘከመ፡ ተናገረቶ፡ ወአጽነዐቶ፡ እምደካመ፡ ፍኖት። ይቤ፡ ቴዎፍሎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ስምዑ፡ አበውየ፡ ወአኀውየ፡ ዘእነግረክሙ፡ በፍርሃት፡ ወበረዓድ፡ ወበሃይማኖት፡ ርትዕት

column4: Vision of Theophilus of Alexandria (continued): Satan urges Herod to pursue the Holy Family.
column15: በእንተ፡ ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ለቴዎፍሎስ፡…. እምድካመ፡ ፍኖት፡…. ወእንዘ፡ ከመዝ፡ አስተርአዮ፡ ሰይጣን፡ ለሄሮድስ፡ ቃለ፡ በቃል

column4: Vision of Theophilus of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family returns from Egypt.
column15: በእንተ፡ ዘከመ፡ አስተርአየቶ፡ ለቴዎፍሎስ፡…. እምድካመ፡ ፍኖት፡…. ወእንዘ፡ ይነውም፡ ዮሴፍ፡ በሌሊት፡ አስተርአዮ፡ መልአከ፡ እግዚአብሔር

column4: Deacon Michael, the grocer and his stolen ring, which Mary helped find in a fish.
The Frenchman whose wife was unable to have children.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ አፍርንጊ፡ እምአድያመ፡ አፍራንሳ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. እምንእሱ፡ ወይትለአካ፡ በኵሉ፡ ኀይሉ። ወሶበ፡ በጽሐ፡ አምጣነ፡ አውስቦ፡ አስተዋሰብዎ፡ አበዊሁ፡ ወለተ፡ እምአውላደ፡ አፍርንጊ

column4: Arabs try to plunder the monasteries of Egypt during the famine of 1120 MM [likely 1404 CE]
column15: ወኮነ፡ በ፲፻፡ ወ፻፡ ወ፳፡ ዓመተ፡ ሰማዕታት፡ ንጹሓን፡ በመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለአብ፡ እግዚእ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ አባ፡ ማቴዎስ፡ ወኮነ፡ በሀገረ፡ ምስር፡ ረሓብ፡ ዐቢይ

column4: Dabra Qaləmon miracles: The monk of Dabra Qaləmon who humbly pretends not to fast and is saved from his brothers by Mary.

column4: Dabra Qaləmon miracles: The monks of Däbrä Qaləmon who were despoiled by Berbers.

column4: Dabra Qaləmon miracles: An Arab steals the scissors of the Jacob the Short, a tailor, of Dabra Qaləmon.

column4: Qommos Raphael from Däbrä ʾƎnṣǝnā and the sacrament of confession.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ስዒድ፡ በደብረ፡ እንጽና፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ በስመ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ወእስከ፡ ይእዜ፡ ሀሎ፡ ወኵሉ፡ አሐዱ፡ አሐዱ፡ የአምሮ፡ ወይሰመይ፡ ምኔተ፡ አቡ፡ ንዕናእ

column4: Däbrä Qaləmon miracles: An Arab who has contempt for Saint Mary’s icon at Däbrä Qaləmon is punished.

column4: The composition of the Maṣḥafa ḥawi by Patriarch Gabriel Ibn Tarīk.
column15: ወኮነ፡ በመዋዕለ፡ አብ፡ ክቡር፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ አባ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ወልደ፡ ተሪክ፡ ወበጽሖ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ በአስ፡ ወጸልእ፡ ምስለ፡ ሕዝቡ

column4: Three Arabs, journeying to Rif on the Nile in Egypt, fall into the water due to a storm and two are saved from crocodiles.
column15: ወኮነ፡ በደብረ፡ ቀልሞን፡ ወሶበ፡ በዝኀ፡ ተአምሪ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ዘታስተርኢ፡ ውስተ፡ ሥዕል፡ ዘሀለወት፡ በደብረ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አባ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ ዘቀልሞን፡ ወፈድፋደሰ፡ ለዐረብ፡ እለ፡ ሀለዉ፡ ዐውዳ

column4: Nəkʷal, the deacon from Margawkim, who spent his master’s money on the poor.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ብእሲ፡ ክርስቲያናዊ፡ ዲያቆን፡ እምሰብአ፡ መርግ፡ ወኬም፡ ወስሙ፡ ንኳል

column4: The priest from Nārdin who was accused because he kept a nun in his house.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ናርዲን፡ ወተሠይመ፡ ቀሲሰ፡ በላዕለ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ድንግል፡ ዘይእቲ፡ ሀገር

column4: The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
The Arab woman who suffered from an issue of blood for many years and is healed by Mary's icon
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ እምአንስተ፡ ዐረብ፡ ወባቲ፡ ውሕዘተ፡ ደም፡ እምብዙኅ፡ ዓመታት

column4: Yoḥannǝs finds a copy of the acts of Saints Juliana and Barbara that he had lost.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ በቤተ፡ ክርስቲያነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ወብፅዕት፡ ንጽሕት፡ ወልዕልት፡ እምሰማዕታት፡ በርባራ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘይሰመይ፡ ዮሐንስ

column4: The lamp before the icon of Saint Mary that the priest tipped over and yet remained suspended
column15: ወሀለወት፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወዓዲ፡ ሥዕል፡ በስመ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. በገቦ፡ ንድቅ፡ ዘየማን

column4: The two blessed monks, Sadaqā and ʾƎstifānos, from the monastery of Saint Victor (Fiqǝṭor); Mary punishes those who steal from and attack them.
column15: ወሀለዉ፡ ክልኤቱ፡ መነኮሳት፡ ቡሩካን፡ እምድብረ፡ ሰማዕት፡ ማር፡ ፊቅጦር፡ በማኅፈደ፡ ናርቆን

column4: The Christians gathered for a feast of Saint Mary are saved from the Arabs.
ʾƎmma Yoḥannǝs and the Ethiopian monk who was on pilgrimage to Jerusalem.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ ብእሲት፡ መሃይምንት፡ ቅድስት፡ ወቡርክት፡ ወተኀድር፡ በአሐዱ፡ ሀገር፡ እምአህጉራተ፡ ታሕታይ፡ ግብጽ፡ ዘትሰመይ፡ ስምባጥ

column4: The European who wanted to steal the bars of the door to the Manger at Bethlehem.

column15: ዘገብረቶ፡ ሥዕለ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ዘእምርት፡ ገባሪታ፡ ተአምራት፡ ወመንክራት፡ ዘደብረ፡ ቀልሞን። ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ተምዐ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ላዕለ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ በእንተ፡ እከዮሙ፡ ወኀጢአቶሙ፡ ለሰብእ፡ እለ፡ ይነብሩ፡ ውስቴታ

column4: The story of the martyr, Saint Victor, and his mother, Martha.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ፈራሂተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወመፍቀሪተ፡ ነዳያን፡ ወመፍቀሪተ፡ ጽድቅ፡ ወምጽዋት፡ ወሥርጉት፡ በኵሉ፡ ምግባረ፡ ሠናይ፡ በጾም፡ ወበጸሎት፡ ዘስማ፡ ማርታ

column4: Elizabeth, the blind daughter of Abraham and Gera Anest of Baderman.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ ሀገር፡ እምአህጉረ፡ ጽዒድ፡ ዘትሰመይ፡ በድርማን፡ ወይነብር፡ ውስቴታ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ አብርሃም፡ ወስመ፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ጌራ፡ አንስት

column4: The widow who could not find husbands for her three daughters.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ ብእሲት፡ ነዳይት፡ ወሞተ፡ ምታ፡ ወኀደገ፡ አዋልደ፡ ለአሐቲ፡ ስማ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለካልእት፡ ስማ፡ ማርታ፡ ወለሣልሲት፡ ስማ፡ የዋሂት

column4: The Arab woman who entrusted her jewels to a Christian for safekeeping.
column15: ወኮነ፡ በሀገረ፡ ጽዒድ፡ ፀብእ፡ ምስለ፡ ዐረብ፡ በበይናቲሆሙ። ወአሐቲ፡ እምአንስተ፡ ዐረብ፡ ነሥአት፡ ሥርጓ፡ ዘወርቅ፡ ወዘብሩር፡ ወአዕቀበቶሙ፡ ኀበ፡ ብእሲት፡ ክርስቲያናዊት

column4: The two brothers who copied the Miracles of Mary and fell into the doing of a sin.
column15: ወሀለዉ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ እምአህጉረ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ፪፡ አኃው፡ ፍቁራን፡ ወጽፉቀ፡ ይትፋቀሩ፡ በበይናቲሆሙ፡ ወየአምሩ፡ ግብረ፡ እድ፡ ወግብረ፡ እዶሙሰ፡ ጽሒፍ

column4: The abbot who did not allow the Miracles of Mary to be read in his monastery.
column15: ወኮነ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ እምአህጉረ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወሀገሩሰ፡ ዐቢይ፡ ይእቲ፡ ወሰብአ፡ ዚአሃ፡ ነገሥታቲሃ፡ ወጳጳሳቲሃ፡ ወኵሉ፡ ሕዝባ፡ እድ፡ ወአንስት፡ ያፈቅርዋ፡ ለእግዝእትነ

column4: Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam miracles: A man killed during the construction of the church of Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam is raised from the dead.
column15: ወእንዘ፡ የሐንጹ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ በደብረ፡ ቍስቋም፡ በስመ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ሶበ፡ አዘዞ፡ ንጉሥ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ እግዚአብሔር

column4: The story of the sorcerers Taludar, who was possessed by a demon.
column15: ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡… እንተ፡ ገብረቶ፡ በላዕለ፡ መሠርይት፡ ጣውሉዳር፡ ወጣማር፡ መርዓታ፡ ለድምሳሴሆን፡ በጽንዐ፡ መዝራዕታ። ነገረ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ዘነገረቶ፡ ለጢሞቴዎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘእለስክንድርያ፡ ወልደ፡ ዲዮስቆሮስ፡ ወትቤ፡ ስማዕ፡ እንግርከ፡ ዘረከበነ፡ አመ፡ ናንሶሱ፡ ውስተ፡ ምድረ፡ ግብጽ

column4: The son of the Muslim ruler of Egypt blasphemes the icon of Saint Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ምስለ፡ ወልዱ፡ በሀገረ፡ ምስር፡ ወውእቱ፡ ተንባላታይ፡ ዕልው፡ በመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለአባ፡ እልስክንድሮስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት

column4: Scete miracles: Eulogius, the stonemason of Scete, Egypt, who used to give hospitality to strangers.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ አውሎጊስ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ወብእሲ፡ ነዳይ፡ ወፀራቤ፡ እብን፡ ውእቱ

column4: Saint Mary appears to Yohannes Kama.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ካማ፡ ዘኀሠሠ፡ እምንእሱ፡ አፍቅሮቶ፡ ለክርስቶስ፡ በዐቢይ፡ ገድል፡ ወአመ፡ ልህቀ፡ ፈኀሩ፡ ሎቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ድንግለ

column4: Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam miracles: The vinedresser of Manfalut who gave his earnings to the builders of Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘይትጌበር፡ አዕጻዳተ፡ ወይን፡ በሀገር፡ ዘትሰመይ፡ መንፈሉጥ፡ ወኮነ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ይነሥእ፡ ዓስቦ፡ እምቈጽለ፡ ገነት

column4: Saint Mary appears as a winged maiden to John, a monk of Saint Macarius.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ቀሲስ፡ በደብረ፡ አባ፡ መቃርስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወዘልፈ፡ ታስተርእዮ፡ እግዝእትነ

column4: Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam miracles: The infidel who stole the lumber from the church at Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ከሐዲ፡ ወየኀድር፡ ውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ ቁስያ፡ ወባዕል፡ ጥቀ፡ በንዋይ፡ ወይጸልእ፡ ዘመደ፡ ክርስቲያን

column4: Saint Mary appears to the martyr, Giyorgis Haddis, in prison.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ መስተጋድል፡ ፈድፋደ፡ በከዊነ፡ ስምዕ፡ በእንተ፡ ስመ፡ እግዝእነ፡ ወአምላክነ፡ ወመድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ሐዲስ

column4: Mareqos, King of Romeya, abandons his throne secretly to become a monk.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ዘነግሠ፡ በሮምያ፡ እምድኅረ፡ ሞተ፡ አቡሁ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ገብረ፡ ኢየሱስ

column4: The people of Romeya appeal to Patriarch Dionysius to find King Mareqos.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘስሙ፡ ዲዮናስዮስ፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮምያ፡ ወሶበ፡ ኃጥእዎ፡ ሕዝብ፡ ለብፁዕ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ሖሩ፡ ኀበ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት

column4: When Sefengeya, wife of King Masfeyanos of Romeya, prays to have a child before the icon of Saint Mary, the icon inclines its head; Sefengeya then conceives Yeshaq (Abba Garima).
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ መስፍያኖስ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ሮምያ፡ ወስመ፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ስፍንግያ፡ እስመ፡ መካን፡ ይእቲ

column4: Entawos, a pagan from Qarays, becomes a Christian after being struck by miraculous arrows.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ አሞራዊ፡ ዘሀገረ፡ ቀራይስ፡ ወአረማዊ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወኢየአምር፡ ለእግዚአብሔር

column4: A man who speaks blasphemously of Saint Mary has his arms and legs cut off.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዕቡይ፡ ዘአንበረ፡ ውስተ፡ ሰማይ፡ አፉሁ፡ ወአንሶሰወ፡ ውስተ፡ ምድር፡ ልሳኑ

column4: The wife of a pagan official who wished to pray at the Holy Sepulcher is prevented until she is baptized.
column15: ኦኵልክሙ፡ ማኅበረ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ክሥቱ፡ አእዛነ፡ አልባቢክሙ፡ ለሰሚዐ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወሰሚዐክሙ፡ ከመ፡ አድኃነቶሙ፡ ለኃጥኣን፡ እምስሕተቶሙ፡ በትንብልናሃ፡ በልዋ፡ ኦድንግል፡ አፍጥኒ

column4: The son of Emperor Tiberius is raised from the dead.
column15: ተአምር፡ ወውዳሴ፡ ክቡር፡ ዘገብረ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ላዕለ፡ እሙ፡ ድንግል። ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ጢባርዮስ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ሮሜ፡ ዘበመዋዕሊሁ፡ ተሰቅለ፡ እግዚእነ

column4: John the Evangelist paints an icon of the Crucifixion for Emperor Tiberius.
column15: ወኮነ፡ ሶበ፡ ሖረ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ኀበ፡ ጢባርዮስ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፡ በከመ፡ ይቤሎ፡ እግዚእነ

column4: Petros Bawares has a vision of the Trinity.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ በዋርስ፡ ወሐነጸ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያነ፡ በስመ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም። ወነበረ፡ ያስተበቍዕ፡ ኀቤሃ፡ ከመ፡ ትስአል፡ ሎቱ፡ ኀበ፡ ወልዳ፡ ያርኢዮ፡ ምስጢረ፡ ሥላሴሁ

column4: The conversion of the Muslim, Rewh, who is renamed Entons Haddis.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ አረማዊ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ርውኅ፡ ወአመ፡ ሜጦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ኀበ፡ አሚነ፡ ሥላሴ፡ በጸሎታ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ተሰምየ፡ እንጦንስሃ፡ ሐዲሰ

column4: The wife of Mark, a priest from Mallawi, is cured of her leprosy.
column15: ተአምር፡ ዘተከሥተት፡ በእደ፡ አቡነ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ አባ፡ ማቴዎስ። ወሀሎ፡ ቀሲስ፡ እምሰብአ፡ መላዊ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ወቦቱ፡ ብእሲት፡ ወመጽአ፡ ላዕሌሃ፡ ለምጽ፡ ዲበ፡ ሕንብርታ

column4: Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam miracles: The monks of Saint Anthony celebrate Holy Week at Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam.
column15: ወበዓመት፡ ፲፻ወ፩፻፡ ፲ወ፪፡ ለሰማዕታት፡ በጽሑ፡ መነኮሳት፡ እምደብረ፡ አቡነ፡ እንጦንዮስ፡ ከመ፡ ይግበሩ፡ ሰሙነ፡ ሕማማት፡ በደብረ፡ ቍስቋም

column4: A Muslim, Katib, tries to extort money from the monks of Saint Anthony.

column4: The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
The sister of Emperor Constantine who prayed to know how Saint Mary bore the Word of God, but then failed to recognize her Son when he appeared to her in church.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ሠናይት፡ ዘትነብር፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘእግዝእትነ፡…. ወታፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. በኵሉ፡ ልባ፡ ወበኵሉ፡ ክሂሎታ፡ ወኮነት፡ ታስተበፅዓ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወትቤላ፡ ብፁዕ፡ አንቲ፡ ኦእግዝእትየ፡ ማርያም፡ ማሪሃም። እፎ፡ ወለድኪዮ፡ ለወልድኪ፡ ዋሕድ፡ ቃለ፡ እግዚአብሔር

column4: The young novice whom Saint Mary encouraged to persevere in his vocation.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ወሬዛ፡ ዘሠናይ፡ አርአያሁ፡ ወያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወይትለአካ፡ በኵሉ፡ ክሂሎቱ፡ እንዘ፡ ሀለወ፡ ውስተ፡ ዓለም፡ እምቅድመ፡ ይመንኵስ። ወእምዝ፡ ሖረ፡ ውስተ፡ ደብር፡ አመከረ፡ ርእሶ፡ አሐተ፡ ዓመተ

column4: The pious official who was accused of embezzlement and of having an affair with the wife of his lord.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ መስፍን፡ በውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ዘሠናይ፡ ግዕዙ፡ ወያፈቅሮ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ወለእግዝእትነ፡…. በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወበኵሉ፡ ክሂሎቱ፡ ወበእንተዝ፡ ጸገዎ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዐቢየ፡ ጸጋ፡ ወወሀቦ፡ ሠናያተ፡ ብዙኃተ። ወቀንኡ፡ ላዕሌሁ፡ እኩያን፡ ሰብእ፡ ወሖሩ፡ ኀበ፡ ንጉሥ

column4: The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ እመ፡ ምኔት፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ደብር፡ እምነ፡ አድባራት፡ ወሀለዋ፡ ውስተ፡ ይእቲ፡ ደብር፡ ብዙኃን፡ ደናግል፡ ወይትኤዘዛ፡ ላቲ። ወኮነት፡ ይእቲ፡ እመ፡ ምኔት፡ ዘሠናይ፡ ግዕዛ

column4: A nun sacristan elopes with a priest, but afterwards they repent.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ደብር፡ ዘደናግል፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ወሀለወት፡ ውስተ፡ ይእቲ፡ ደብር፡ ብእሲት፡ ሠናይት፡ መነኮሳዪት፡ ፈራሂተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወትትለአክ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያና፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. መስተሣህልት፡ እመ፡ ኵሉ፡ ፍሥሐ፡ ወሐሤት። ወኮነ፡ ይእቲ፡ መንኮሳዪት፡ ተዐጥን፡ ሥዕላ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ወትኤምኅ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ወትሰግድ፡ ቅድሜሃ

column4: The bee keeper who consulted a sorceress to have more honey.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ እፍልንድር፡ ወኮነ፡ ይፈቅድ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩን፡ ሎቱ፡ መዐረ፡ ወስምዓ፡ ብዙኃ፡ ፈድፋደ፡ እምኵሉ፡ አግዋሪሁ

column4: The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ መነኮስ፡ ውስተ፡ ደብር፡ እምነ፡ አድባራተ፡ እስክንድርያ፡ ወኮነ፡ ያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወሶበ፡ ይዜክሩ፡ ስማ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወኮነ፡ ይገርር፡ ላቲ፡ ወከማሁ፡ ውእቱኒ፡ ሶበ፡ ይዜክር፡ ስማ፡ ኮነ፡ ይደንን፡ በገጹ

column4: The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ መነኮስ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐዱ፡ ደብር፡ እምነ፡ አድባራት፡ ወኮነ፡ ያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወይትለአካ፡ በኵሉ፡ ክሂሎቱ፡ ወያስተጣዕም፡ ጸሎታ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወሶበ፡ ይዜክር፡ ስማ፡ ይትፌሣሕ፡ ወይትሐሠይ። ወኮነ፡ ውእቱ፡ መነኮስ፡ ጸሐፌ፡ መጻሕፍት፡ ዘደብር

column4: The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፡ ወኮነ፡ ብእሲ፡ ሠናየ፡ ወጻድቀ፡ ወይፈርሆ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ ወየዐቅብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ እምኵሉ፡ ሕሊናት፡ ርኩሳት

column4: A nun in prison for her faith prays for two virgins.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ሠናይት፡ ፈራሂተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወታፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. በኵሉ፡ ልባ። ወአስተዋደይዋ፡ ሰብእ፡ እኩያን፡ ለይእቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ኀበ፡ ብልካርያ፡ ንግሥት፡ ርኩስት፡ ወአምቅሕዋ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ሞቅሕ

column4: The sinful woman who despaired when she kept on sinning and swallowed a scorpion.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ኃጥእት፡ ወትገብር፡ ኃጢአተ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ። ወኮነ፡ ትትመነደብ፡ በገቢረ፡ ኃጢአተ፡ እስመ፡ ይእቲ፡ ኮነት፡ ትኔስሕ፡ ወትትመየጥ፡ ውስተ፡ ገቢረ፡ ኃጢአት

column4: The prudent monk who suspected that the food that the monks were eating was harmful, but then saw Saint Mary making it tasty for them.
column15: ወሀለወ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ጠቢብ፡ ወመነኮስ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐዱ፡ ደብር፡ ወፈተወ፡ ከመ፡ ይንብር፡ ውስተ፡ ይእቲ፡ ደብር፡ ወይሜግብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ በጥበበ፡ ዚአሁ። ወተሐረመ፡ ከመ፡ ኢይብላዕ፡ እምመባልዕት፡ ዘይበልዑ፡ መነኮሳት

column4: The woman who was prevented from fasting by her husband.
column15: ተብህለ፡ በእንተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ከመ፡ ይእቲ፡ በፅዓት፡ ነፍሳ፡ ከመ፡ ትጹም፡ ጾመ፡ እግዝእትነ፡…. ወሶበ፡ ጾመት፡ አእመረ፡ ምታ፡ ከመ፡ ይእቲ፡ ትጸውም፡ ሐዘነ፡ ላዕሌሃ፡ ወከልኣ፡ እምጾም

column4: The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ክብርት፡ እምዘመደ፡ ክቡራን፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ በጽንፈ፡ ባሕር፡ ዘየዐቢ፡ ወዘመዳ፡ ለይእቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ይከብሩ፡ እምሰብአ፡ ይእቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ወባቲ፡ ምታ፡ እምክቡራነ፡ ሰብእ፡ ወሊቃውንት፡ ዐበይት

column4: The rich merchant from Constantinople who lost all his money and made the icon of Saint Mary his guarantor when he borrowed money from a usurer.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ በውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ ቍስጥንጥንያ፡ ብእሲ፡ ባዕል፡ ወኮነ፡ ሎቱ፡ ዐርካ፡ ክቡር፡ መስፍን፡ እምዐበይተ፡ ይእቲ፡ ሀገር

column4: Saint Mary saves from a lion a pious monk who had drunk too much wine.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ መነኮስ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ደብር፡ ወኮነ፡ ይትለአካ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. መስተምሕርት፡ ወመስተሣህልት፡ ወያፈቅራ፡ በኵሉ፡ ልቡ። ወበአሐቲ፡ ዕለት፡ እምዕለታት፡ ሰትየ፡ ውእቱ፡ መነኮስ፡ ወይነ፡ ወሰክረ

column4: A ship that was about to founder is saved when they pray to Saint Mary.
The monk who was custodian of a church near a river and drowned while trying to cross to visit his lover.
The Jew who attacked the icon of Saint Mary when he failed to obtain by litigation someone else's property.
column15: ተብህለ፡፡ ከመ፡፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ መስተቃሕው፡ አይሁዳዊ፡ ወበአሐቲ፡ ዕለት፡ ተቀሐወ፡ ምስለ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ወተመውአ፡ ውእቱ፡ አይሁዳዊ፡ ወፈደየ፡ ንዋየ፡ ብዙኃ፡ ለውእቱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዘተቀሐወ፡ ምስሌሁ

column4: The husband who broke his vow that he would live celibately with his wife.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ባዕል፡ ዘቦቱ፡ ብእሲተ፡ ክብርተ፡ ወሠናይተ፡ ወበጽሑ፡ ክልኤሆሙ፡ እስከ፡ ርሥእና፡ ተካየዱ፡ በበይናቲሆሙ፡ ከመ፡ ይዕቀቡ፡ ሥጋሆሙ፡ በንጽሕና

column4: The nun who used to pray for the dead, but lost her virginity and died before completing her penance.
The nun whom Saint Mary admonished to recite the Hail Mary more attentively.
The knight who denied Christ at the bidding of Satan, in order to have fine clothes for a reception, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
The pious rich man whom Satan served in hopes of destroying him.
The merchant who distributed as alms the money that had been loaned him by a friend.
The peasant who became rich from other people's goods.
The two brothers from Rome, Peter, a deacon, and Stephen, an avaricious magistrate.
The hypocritical superior of a monastery who pretended to be religious.
The woman from Rome who killed the baby she bore after sleeping with her son
The Jew of Constantinople who threw an icon of Saint Mary into the latrine.
Saint Mary saves the soul of a rich sinner who had repented and was planning to build a monastery and become a monk.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ፈረሳዊ፡ ክቡር፡ ወባዕል፡ ዘቦቱ፡ ንዋያተ፡ ወአእጻዳተ፡ ወኢይገብር፡ ወኢምንተኒ፡ እምሠናያት፡ ወኮነ፡ ይጸልእ፡ አብያተ፡ ክርስቲያናት፡ ወነዳያነ፡ ወምስኪናነ፡ ወያፈቅር፡ ተውኔተ፡ ወማኅሌተ፡ ወትፍግዕተ

column23: This mss has two stories with ID 153, on ff. 13r and 111v. Macomber gave incipits of one of the two stories, but he didn't specify a folio number. So currently both instances have identical incipits in the spreadsheet and the ITool.

ʾƎmma Yoḥannǝs and the Ethiopian monk who was on pilgrimage to Jerusalem.

The story of the two brothers from Dalga who were dyers.
Homily of John Chrysostom on the visit of Saint Mary and her Son to John the Baptist.
The story of Pifamon, the martyr from Awsim.
The story of John, the martyr from Senhut.
The Jews plot to burn the body of Saint Mary.
A Roman official is prevented from approaching the Holy Sepulcher.

A priest is warned by an angel not to rush when incensing the icon of Saint Mary.

The story of the Muslim who lived near the churches of Saints Mark and Shenute.

Patriarch Abraham and the interpretation of the parable of the mustard seed.
The daughter of the rich man from Caesarea who could not deliver her baby.

The woman from Cairo who lived by the river and whose daughter became blind.
A poor woman with a broken leg is healed by the icon of Saint Mary in the church of Harat ar-Rum.
The virgin who sinned with many lovers.
The brigands who killed each other at the miraculous spring.
The son of a rich official of Cappadocia is raised from the dead.
The beggar at the church of Qirqos in Amhara from whose head a horn grew.
Mary, Assumption of Cycle: The Apostles gather for the funeral of Saint Mary.
The merchant from Senfewat who struck the icon of Saint Mary.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: When Tafoneya lays hands on the bier of Saint Mary, an angel cuts his arms off.
The reopening of the church in Harat Zuwayla.
The healing of the Egyptian King Soforon (or Safron).
King Dawit miracles: The miracle concerning the golden ink during the reign of King Dawit.
The chastisement of the heretic, Nestorius.
Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil and the rich man who refused to give him a tablet [saleda] for an icon of Saint Mary.
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The man who was possessed by a spirit of epilepsy [nagargar] for 47 years.
Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil and the Jewish merchant of Caesarea who stole a golden plate from the church, but later became a Christian.
The miraculous spring of Mehzab.
The story of Saint Menas and his brother.

column4: The election of Patriarch Matthew I.
The story of Saint Alexius [Abdo l a-Masih], son of Emperor Theodosius.
The faded icon of Saint Mary that the mother-in-law wanted to discard.
The woman from Cairo whose nine children all died; Mary helped her conceive three more.
Holy Family journey cycle: The places in Egypt visited by the Holy Family.
The nominal Christian from Sidon who encountered a dragon.
The sinful deacon who was healed by a drop of Saint Mary's milk.
The thief whom the king's soldiers could not kill.
The Emperor of Rome who erected an altar in his palace.
Saint Mary commands a deacon to give Christian burial to a sinful deacon assassinated by his enemies; when they disinter him, a flower is found in his mouth.
The repentant knight who could pray only the Hail Mary.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
The bishop for whom Saint Mary tailored a new sackcloth sends a penitent to Santiago.
The deacon's prayer that contained five times "Rejoice!" [tafassehiyat].
Alexander, a Jew from Jerusalem, is delivered three days after he was swallowed up by a dragon.
The pilgrim to Santiago whom Satan persuaded to mutilate himself after falling into a sexual sin.
The priest who could only say the Mass of the Virgin Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ካህን፡ ቀሲስ፡ በሀገረ፡ ቂሳርያ፡ ዘስሙ፡ እንድርያስ፡ ወሀሎ፡ በህየ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘተሐንጸ፡ በስማ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡…. ወብዙኅ፡ ሰብእ፡ ካህናት፡ ወዲያቆናት፡ ይትጋብኡ፡ ውስቴታ፡ ወይነግሩ፡ በእንተ፡ ዕበየ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ዘትገብር፡ እስመ፡ ውእቱ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ እንድርያስ፡ ኢየአምር፡ ካልአ፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ቅዳሴሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም

column4: The knight who wanted to seduce the daughter of the cobbler.
The Jewish boy who received Holy Communion with his Christian companions.
The pregnant woman who was caught by the tide while going to the church of Saint Michael (Mont Saint Michel)
A man who drowned when a pilgrim ship sank is resuscitated.
The divorced wife who prayed for revenge against her rival.
The woman from Rome whose daughter rose up on the anniversary of her death.
The widow who prayed to Saint Mary and saved her only son from death by hanging.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
The sister of Emperor Constantine who prayed to know how Saint Mary bore the Word of God, but then failed to recognize her Son when he appeared to her in church.
The young novice whom Saint Mary encouraged to persevere in his vocation.
The pious official who was accused of embezzlement and of having an affair with the wife of his lord.
The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
A nun sacristan elopes with a priest, but afterwards they repent.
The bee keeper who consulted a sorceress to have more honey.
The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
A nun in prison for her faith prays for two virgins.
The sinful woman who despaired when she kept on sinning and swallowed a scorpion.
The prudent monk who suspected that the food that the monks were eating was harmful, but then saw Saint Mary making it tasty for them.
The woman who was prevented from fasting by her husband.
The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
The rich merchant from Constantinople who lost all his money and made the icon of Saint Mary his guarantor when he borrowed money from a usurer.
Saint Mary saves from a lion a pious monk who had drunk too much wine.
The husband who broke his vow that he would live celibately with his wife.
The merchant who distributed as alms the money that had been loaned him by a friend.
The two brothers from Rome, Peter, a deacon, and Stephen, an avaricious magistrate.
Saint Mary saves the soul of a rich sinner who had repented and was planning to build a monastery and become a monk.
Pachomius, the avaricious patriarch of Rome, who sold the chrism of the church.
The avaricious priest who visited a dying man who loved bribes.
The nun who was dissuaded from eloping with a knight by a vision of Hell.
The shepherd near the church of Saint Paul in Rome who was possessed by a demon.
The monk who has carried by the bretheren to church when he became too sick to walk.
The rich knight who was advised by an abbot to pray to Saint Mary to win the heart of the woman with whom he was in love.
The monk custodian of the church who prayed to see Saint Mary.
The bankrupt merchant to whom Satan offered two pearls if he would deny Christ and Saint Mary.
A herdsman saves his beasts in a storm by praying to Saint Mary.
The pious mower of hay to whom the gatekeeper gave his daughter in marriage.
The rich woman who went with the monks to the manbalis for prayer and there saw a vision of Saint Mary.
The robber whom a bishop was commanded to bury after he was executed.
The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
The Jewish cowherd who was baptized by his Christian companions.
The mighty Goliath threatens to destroy the monastery of Saint Mary.
The Muslim who found an icon of Saint Mary in his house.
The only son of a king who dedicated himself to Saint Mary.
The young man who was ready to serve Satan, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
A knight tries to seduce the wife of a friend, but she is saved by a vision.
The pious rich man whom Satan served in hopes of destroying him.
The peasant who became rich from other people's goods.
The hypocritical superior of a monastery who pretended to be religious.
The Jew of Constantinople who threw an icon of Saint Mary into the latrine.
The woman from Rome who killed the baby she bore after sleeping with her son
The monk who got himself appointed abbot of another monastery by the king, without the consent of the monks.
The young man who offered the ring he had received from his girlfriend to the icon of Saint Mary.
A ship that was about to founder is saved when they pray to Saint Mary.
The Jew who attacked the icon of Saint Mary when he failed to obtain by litigation someone else's property.
The knight who denied Christ at the bidding of Satan, in order to have fine clothes for a reception, but refused to deny Saint Mary.
The monk who was custodian of a church near a river and drowned while trying to cross to visit his lover.
The nun who used to pray for the dead, but lost her virginity and died before completing her penance.
The nun whom Saint Mary admonished to recite the Hail Mary more attentively.
The monk who saved the church of Saint Mary in Atrib by his prayers when its destruction had been ordered by the Caliph.
Abba Mardari, who overheard twelve angels talking about going to Constantinople to hear Saint John Chrysostom praise Saint Mary.
The wealthy man to whom Saint Mary appeared in the form of a bird to save the countryside from pestilence.

Thecla cycle: Saint Mary incenses Thecla (continuation).

Saint Paul is taken to the third heaven and there sees Saint Mary.
Abba Behor has a vision of Saint Mary.
Vision of Gregory the Seer [ra'eya hebu'at].
Saint Mary appears to Sawla, the wife of the martyr, Giyorgis Haddis.
The history ot Däbrä Mahew near Jerusalem and its miraculous spring.
The story of Awr, the son of the princess and the magician, Abrasit.
Saint Mary cures the son of a Roman official in Bethlehem.
Saint Mary heals a woman possessed by evil spirits.
An Egyptian woman comes to Saint Mary in Bethlehem and is healed of her fever.
A woman whose right eye had been blinded by a demon is healed by Saint Mary.
Saint Mary appears to Timothy, Patriarch of Alexandria, in the church of Saint Pachomius in Alexandria.

The priest who left the keys of the church locked up inside.

Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The flight into Egypt.

Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family crosses the Nile at Asmunayn.
Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Christ Child grants Saint Mary a vision of his future glory.

Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): Ahrufas, the guardian angel of Egypt, comes to the Holy Family.
Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The experience of the Holy Family in the district of Asmunayn.
Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family encounters thieves.
Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family arrives at Däbrä QWesqWam.
Saint Peter gives Saint John Chrysostom the keys of the kingdom and Saint John the Evangelist gives him the Gospels; then Saint Mary appears to him.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: The Jews try to burn down the house where Saint Mary is staying but are burned up instead.
The Holy Spirit recounts the salvific events that have occurred on Sunday.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays with the disciples.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays with the disciples (continuation).
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays for the release of the souls in judgment.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint John the Evangelist sees a vision of Saint Mary in glory.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Christ celebrates Mass for Saint Mary.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary asks Christ that the disciples preach her Transitus and Assumption.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary asks that Saint John be allowed to visit her dwelling place.

Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary prays to be taken from this life.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: The Jews go to Bethlehem to seize Saint Mary but are blinded.

Christ makes Saint Peter head of the Church.

Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil finds the buried icon of Saint Mary.
Saint Basil cycle: Saint Mary tells Saint Basil to take two pillars from a pagan temple.
Saint Basil cycle: Saint Mary sets up the pillars in the church and makes a miraculous spring flow out at their base.

Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint John the Evangelist sees Christ kissing Saint Mary's burial cloth.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Saint Mary's soul descends from heaven in a tent of light.
Saint John Chrysostom defends a woman whom Nestorius had told the people to spit upon.

Saint Mary rescues the ship in which Mar Barsuma is travelling.
Saint Mary appears to the disciples of Mar Barsuma in the form of a dove.
Saint Mary appears to Saints Atrasis and Yona, virgins and martyrs.
Saint Mary appears to Saint Sarabamon, the future bishop of Nikiou and martyr.

Saint Mary appears to Saint Paphnutius.

A nun in prison for her faith prays for two virgins.
Saint Mary appears to Saint Theodore the Anatolian.
The fate of the monk, Giyorgis, who followed the teachings of Za-Mika'el.
Vision of a certain saint about the fate of a priest who swore falsely.
Abbas sees a vision of Saint Mary blessing the monks who were chanting the Psalms.

Zärˀa Yaˁəqob miracles: The judgment of the court of Zärˀa Yaˁəqob against the Stephanites.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Synaxary entry for 16 Nahase: The Apostles visit Saint Mary in heaven.
Mary, Assumption of cycle: Anonymous homily against the report that the Apostles abandoned the body of Saint Mary when they were attacked by the Jews during her funeral procession.
A Christian community is attacked by a neighboring Muslim community.
A renegade monk who had become a Jew is hunted down by the troops of the king.
A Jew is led to baptism by a dream about a lion and a monk; afterwards he curses a Jew at the latter's request.
The Magicians who tried to cast a spell on the Epiphany water.
Zärˀa Yaˁəqob miracles: The birth of the prince, Batergela Maryam.
Zärˀa Yaˁəqob miracles: Zärˀa Yaˁəqob and Batergela Maryam, who is accused of treason and is imprisoned but delivered from the plague.
Zärˀa Yaˁəqob miracles: Zärˀa Yaˁəqob and Batergela Maryam, who is protected from the plague; his calumniator is punished by the king.
Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The Holy Family arrives at Däbrä Qʷəsqʷam.
When Satan destroys the oven of a monastery, he is compelled to serve the monks for twelve years in punishment.
Däbrä Metmaq miracles: Saint Mary shows those assembled at Däbrä Metmaq a negative vision of Mohammad
The daughter of the rich man from Caesarea who could not deliver her baby.
The five sorrows of Saint Mary.
The sinner whom Saint Mary healed after his relatives had spent all his money on physicians.
Saint Mary gives a garment to a poor monk.
Vision of Timothy of Alexandria (continued): The flight into Egypt.
A child whom his mother had vowed to Saint Mary is rescued from drowning.
A column falls and breaks the leg of the son of an official when Muslims destroy a church of Saint Mary in Homs.
The old woman from Sembat who gave the offering for Saint Mary to Saint George.
Emperor Arcadius and the golden statue of Saint Mary; he asks Saint John Chrysostom to expound on Matthew 1: 25.
A thief is hanged upside down with the objects he stole from the church of Saint Mary in Sebkahad.
The priest from Cyprus who brought a particle of the Eucharist to a Jew.
The conversion of the Muslim, Rewh, who is renamed Entons Haddis.
Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil and the Jewish merchant of Caesarea who stole a golden plate from the church, but later became a Christian.
The election of Patriarch Matthew I.
Mary, Pregnancy of cycle: Saint Mary is found to be pregnant.
Zärˀa Yaˁəqob miracles:  Zärˀa Yaˁəqob and the invasion of Badlay.
The Stephanites in Egypt and Palestine.

column4: Scete miracles: Eulogius, the stonemason of Scete, Egypt, who used to give hospitality to strangers.
Homily of John Chrysostom on the visit of Saint Mary and her Son to John the Baptist.
The story of John, the martyr from Senhut.
The persecution of the Christians during the patriarchate of Cosmas II.
Holy Family journey cycle: The king of Egypt asks Saint Mary to bless his land.
Holy Family journey cycle: The places in Egypt visited by the Holy Family.
Saint Mary appears to the gabaz of her church in Waybela and tells him about the fall of Badlay.
The merchant from Senfewat who struck the icon of Saint Mary.
King Dawit miracles: The miracle concerning the golden ink during the reign of King Dawit.
Emperor Zärˀa Yaˁəqob is given a sign of Badlay's fall.
The priest from Nārdin who was accused because he kept a nun in his house.
Yoḥannǝs finds a copy of the acts of Saints Juliana and Barbara that he had lost.
The wife of Joseph from Mǝneta Diyāqon, who had no male children.
Amnut, the custodian of a church in Egypt, quarrels with his bishop.
The wife of Joseph from Mǝneta Diyāqon, who had no male children.
Scete miracles: Emperor Zeno builds churches in Scete.
Scete miracles: Saint Mary blesses Scete, which Saint Macarius chooses for his monastery.
The story of Michael, the scribe who converted to Islam when he was beaten.
When Pariqos of Fesa confesses his sins to the bishop, the latter, refusing him absolution, tells him to go to Abba Yaceqob (Santiago).
Christ, Nativity of cycle: How the Virgin Mary gave birth (see no. 299) (347, 445 similar)
Christ, Nativity of cycle: The shepherds and the magi come to worship Christ. (299, 446 similar)
The beggar at the church of Qirqos in Amhara from whose head a horn grew.
Saint Mary heals a servant girl from a magic spell.
Sara from Mesot, who became insane and went about naked.
Mary, Childhood of cycle: When she is three years old, Saint Mary is taken to the Temple. (315, 316-D, 447 similar)
Samuˀel of Wali miracles: Christ orders Abba Samu'el of Wali to celebrate Mass for the feast of Saint Mary.

Däbrä Metmaq miracles: The annual apparition of Saint Mary at Däbrä Metmaq (continued)

column4: Däbrä Metmaq miracles: The annual apparition of Saint Mary at Däbrä Metmaq: The people start to beat a serving girl, in order to take from her the kerchief that she had received back from Saint Mary after tossing it to her.

column4: Saint Mary comes to a church in the form of a white dove to heal from smallpox a man whose only good work was celebrating her commemoration.
When Agabos from Dalga enters the church, the icon of Saint Mary weeps.

column4: Zärˀa Yaˁəqob miracles: Zärˀa Yaˁəqob institutes monthly feasts of Saint Mary.
The son of a rich official of Cappadocia is raised from the dead.
Saint Mary appears during Mass in the church at Meneta Sard.
The Ethiopian pilgrim who was expelled from the Church (of the Resurrection) in Jerusalem during the Easter services.
The rich man who left the church because the priest was saying the Anaphora of Saint Mary, Gwasca, on a big feast day.
The rich persons who stored their wealth in a church.
The three pious priests and monks who wore fine clothes.
The punishment of an Ethiopian woman who swore falsely that she had not committed adultery with another woman's husband.
Christ, Nativity of cycle: The nativity of Christ. (347, 445 similar)
The icon of Saint Mary in the church of the "Romans" that rebuked the Ethiopians for approaching with their shoes on.
Ark of Zion cycle: When Israel Sins against the Law, the Philistines defeat them and carry off the Ark of Zion, which then chastizes them.

column22: 1; not of story, of madonna and child
column23: Frontispiece full-page miniature (with Ethiopic captions above and below) on f. 177v: The Virgin and Child.   Ornamental band (harag) decorating the incipit page of  the miracle (f. 178rab).  Numeral ፳ወ፮, numbering the miracle፡archaic aspect of the numeral ፮: it has the loop open, looking like a “compressed” ፯.   Place name mentioned: እፍልንድር፡ ˀƎflǝndǝr.  Kropp: In the land of Aflandar (Flanders) beekeeper (but it's a farmer) ask for honey and wax.

column4: The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ መነኮስ፡ ውስተ፡ ደብር፡ እምነ፡ አድባራተ፡ ሀገረ፡ እስክንድርያ፨ ወኮነ፡ ያፈቅራ፡... በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፨ ወሶበ፡ ይዜክሩ፡ ስማ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ማሪሃም፡ ኮነ፡ ይገርር፡ ላቲ፨ ወከማሁ፡ ውእቱኒ፡ ሶበ፡...

column4: The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ መነኮስ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐዱ፡ ደብር፡ እምነ፡ አድባራት፨ ወኮነ፡ ያፈቅራ፡ ... በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወይትለአካ፡ በኵሉ፡ ክሂሎቱ፡ ወያስተጥዕም፡ ጸሎታ፡... ወሶበ፡ ይዜክር፡ ስማ፡ ይትፌሣሕ፡ ወይትሐሠይ ፨ ወኮነ፡ ውእቱ፡ መነኮስ፡ ይሐፌ፡ መጻሕፍት፡  …
column17: (F. 180rb l. 12) ፳ወ፰፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ …  (l. 18) ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ መነኮስ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐዱ፡ ደብር፡ እምነ፡ አድባራት፨ ወኮነ፡ ያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ (f. 180va)ማርያም፡ ማሪሃም፡ በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወይትለአካ፡ በኵሉ፡ ክሂሎቱ፡ ወያስተጥዕም፡ ጸሎታ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም፡ ማሪሃም፡ ወሶበ፡ ይዜክር፡ ስማ፡ ይትፌሣሕ፡ ወይትሐሠይ ፨ ወኮነ፡ ውእቱ፡ መነኮስ፡ ይሐፌ፡ መጻሕፍት፡  …

column4: The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፨  ወኮነ፡ ብእሴ፡ ሠናየ፡ ወጻድቀ፡ ወይፈርሆ፡ ለእግዚእብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ ወየዐቅብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ እምኵሉ፡ ሕሊናት፡ ርኩሳት፨ ወዘአሐቲ፡ ዕለት፡ እምነ፡ …
column17: (F. 181rb l. 15)፳ወ፱፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ …  (l. 21) ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፨  ወኮነ፡ ብ(f. 181va)እሴ፡ ሠናየ፡ ወጻድቀ፡ ወይፈርሆ፡ ለእግዚእብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ ወየዐቅብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ እምኵሉ፡ ሕሊናት፡ ርኩሳት፨ ወዘአሐቲ፡ ዕለት፡ እምነ፡ …
column18: The incipit of the miracle in EMML 9002 is matching with the incipit of the miracle in manuscript EMML  7089 f. 36v (Macomber ID 163 "Short form"), but not with the incipit of the miracle in EMML 3872 f. 55v (Macomber ID 163).  Both EMML 7089 and EMML 3872 (this with two miracles  ID 163 =  two redactions of the story) are manuscripts used by Macomber for the ID 163.

column4: A nun in prison for her faith prays for two virgins.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ሠናይት፡ ፈራሂተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፨ ወታፈቅራ፡ ... በኵሉ፡ ልባ፨ ወአስተዋደይዋ፡ ሰብእ፡ እኩያን፡ ለይእቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ኀበ፡ ብልካርያ፡ ንግሥት፡ ርኵስት፡ ወአሞቅሕዋ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ሞቅሕ፨ …
column17: (F. 182vb l. 10)፴፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ …  (l. 21) ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ሠናይት፡ ፈራሂተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፨ ወታፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም፡ ማሪሃም፡ በኵሉ፡ ልባ፨ ወአስተዋደይዋ፡ ሰ(f. 183ra)ብእ፡ እኩያን፡ ለይእቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ኀበ፡ ብልካርያ፡ ንግሥት፡ ርኵስት፡ ወአሞቅሕዋ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ሞቅሕ፨…

column4: The sinful woman who despaired when she kept on sinning and swallowed a scorpion.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ኀጥእት፡ ወትገብር፡ ኀጢአተ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ፨ ወኮነት፡ ትትመነደብ፡ በገቢረ፡ ኀጢአት፨ እስመ፡ ይእቲ፡ ኮነት፡ ትኔስሕ፡ ወትትመየጥ፡ ውስተ፡ ኀጢአታ፡ ብዙኀ፡ ጊዜ፨ …
column17: (F. 183vb l. 20) ፴ወ፩፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ …  (f. 184ra l. 3) ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ኀጥእት፡ ወትገብር፡ ኀጢአተ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ፨ ወኮነት፡ ትትመነደብ፡ በገቢረ፡ ኀጢአት፨ እስመ፡ ይእቲ፡ ኮነት፡ ትኔስሕ፡ ወትትመየጥ፡ ውስተ፡ ኀጢአታ፡ ብዙኀ፡ ጊዜ፨ …

column4: The prudent monk who suspected that the food that the monks were eating was harmful, but then saw Saint Mary making it tasty for them.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ጠቢብ፨ ወመንኰሰ፡ ውስተ፡  አሐዱ፡ ደብር፡ ወፈቀደ፡ ከመ፡ ይንበር፡ ውስተ፡ ውእቱ፡ ደብር፡ ወይመግብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ በጥበበ፡ ዚአሁ፡ ወተኀረመ፡ ከመ፡ ኢይብላዕ፡ መባልዕት፡ …
column17: (F. 185ra l. 20) ፴ወ፪፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ …  (f. 185rb l. 3) ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ጠቢብ፨ ወመንኰሰ፡ ውስተ፡  አሐዱ፡ ደብር፡ ወፈቀደ፡ ከመ፡ ይንበር፡ ውስተ፡ ውእቱ፡ ደብር፡ ወይመግብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ በጥበበ፡ ዚአሁ፡ ወተኀረመ፡ ከመ፡ ኢይብላዕ፡ መባልዕት፡ …
column18: The incipit of the miracle in EMML 9002 is matching with the incipit of the miracle in manuscript EMML  7089 f.  42r (Macomber ID 166), not with the incipit of EMML  3872  f 57v (Macomber ID 166).

column4: The woman who was prevented from fasting by her husband.
column15: ተብህለ፡ በእንተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ከመ፡ ይእቲ፡ በፅዐት፡ ነፍሳ፡ ከመ፡ ትጹም፡ ጾመ፡ ... ወሶበ፡ ጾመት፡ አእመረ፡ ሞታ፡ ከመ፡ ይእቲ፡ ትጸውም፡ ሐዘነ፡ ላዕሌሃ፡ ወካልአ፡ እምጾም፡ ወአገበራ፡ ከመ፡ ትብላዕ፡ ወገሠጻ፡ ከመ፡ ኢትጹም፨…
column17: (F. 186va l. 19) ) ፴ወ፫፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ …  (f. 186vb l. 2) ተብህለ፡ በእንተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ከመ፡ ይእቲ፡ በፅዐት፡ ነፍሳ፡ ከመ፡ ትጹም፡ ጾመ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም፡ ማሪሃም፡ ወሶበ፡ ጾመት፡ አእመረ፡ ሞታ፡ ከመ፡ ይእቲ፡ ትጸውም፡ ሐዘነ፡ ላዕሌሃ፡ ወካልአ፡ እምጾም፡ ወአገበራ፡ ከመ፡ ትብላዕ፡ ወገሠጻ፡ ከመ፡ ኢትጹም፨…

column4: The noblewoman who was persuaded by her spiritual father to give away her fine clothes.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ክብርት፡ እምዘመድ፡ ክቡራን፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ በጽንፈ፡ ባሕር፡ ዘየዓቢ፨ ወዘመዳ፡ ለይእቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ይከብሩ፡ እምኵሎሙ፡ ሰብአ፡ ይእቲ፡ ሀገር፨ ወባቲ፡ ሞተ፡ እምክቡራን፡ ሰብእ፡ ወሊቃውንት፡ ዓበይት፨ ….
column17: (F. 187va l. 21) ፴ወ፬፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ …  (f. 187vb l. 4) ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ክብርት፡ እምዘመድ፡ ክቡራን፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ በጽንፈ፡ ባሕር፡ ዘየዓቢ፨ ወዘመዳ፡ ለይእቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ይከብሩ፡ እምኵሎሙ፡ ሰብአ፡ ይእቲ፡ ሀገር፨ ወባቲ፡ ሞተ፡ እምክቡራን፡ ሰብእ፡ ወሊቃውንት፡ ዓበይት፨ ….
column18: The incipit of the miracle in EMML 9002 is matching with the incipit of the miracle (= ID 168) in manuscript EMML  7089 f. 45v (ms. used by Macomber), not with the incipit of the miracle (ID 168) in EMML  3872 f. 59v (other ms. used by Macomber).

column4: The rich merchant from Constantinople who lost all his money and made the icon of Saint Mary his guarantor when he borrowed money from a usurer.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ በውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ ቈስጠንጥንያ፡ ብእሲ፡ ባዕል፡ ወኮነ፡ ሎቱ፡ ዓርክ፡ ክቡር፡ መስፍን፡ እምዐበይተ፡ ይእቲ፡ ሀገር፨ ወኮነ፡ ውእቱ፡ ባዕል፡ ያፈቅሮ፡ ለውእቱ፡ መስፍን፡ ፈድፋደ፡ ወያበ* ሎቱ፡ አምኃ፡ ብ* ጊዜ፡ ወይበልዕ፡ …
column17: (F. 190rb l. 16) ፴ወ፭፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ …  (f. 190rb l. 23) ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ (f. 190va) በውስተ፡ ሀገረ፡ ቈስጠንጥንያ፡ ብእሲ፡ ባዕል፡ ወኮነ፡ ሎቱ፡ ዓርክ፡ ክቡር፡ መስፍን፡ እምዐበይተ፡ ይእቲ፡ ሀገር፨ ወኮነ፡ ውእቱ፡ ባዕል፡ ያፈቅሮ፡ ለውእቱ፡ መስፍን፡ ፈድፋደ፡ ወያበ{n.l.} ሎቱ፡ አምኃ፡ ብ{n.l.} ጊዜ፡ ወይበልዕ፡ …    Abbreviation used: n.l. = non liquet ("not legible").
column18: Place name Constantinople: different spelling in the miracle in EMML 9002: ቈስጠንጥንያ፡Qʷasṭanṭǝnyā;  the name is written as ቍስጥንጥንያ፡Qʷǝsṭǝnṭǝnyā in the miracle in EMML 7089 f. 49v (manuscript used by Macomber for the ID 169).

column4: Saint Mary saves from a lion a pious monk who had drunk too much wine.

column18: The incipit of the miracle in EMML 9002 is matching with the incipit of the miracle (= ID 170) in manuscript EMML 7089 f. 55v (ms. used by Macomber), not with the incipit of the miracle (= ID 170) in  3872 62v (other ms. used by Macomber). The name of the monk, i.d. ጢሞቴዎስ፡ Ṭimotewos, appearing in the incipit of 3872 f. 62v, is omitted in EMML  9002 as well as in EMML 7089.

column4: The husband who broke his vow that he would live celibately with his wife.

column4: The nun who used to pray for the dead, but lost her virginity and died before completing her penance.

column4: The young man who offered the ring he had received from his girlfriend to the icon of Saint Mary.
column15: ተብህለ፡   ከመ፡ ሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ምዝብርት፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፨ ወፈቀዱ፡ ከመ፡ ይሕንጽዋ፡ ዳግመ፡ ወአንበሩ፡ ሥዕለ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ... ቅድመ፡ አንቀጸ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፨ እስመ፡ ኵሉ፡ ዘየኀልፍ፡ በውስተ፡ ፍኖት፡ ከመ፡ ያንብር፡ ምጽዋተ፡ በእንተ፡ ሕንጻ፡  ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፨ ወሀለወት፡ ቅድመ፡ ይእቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡…

column4: The rich man who threw dry bread to a beggar in the name of Saint Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ባዕል፡ ጥቀ፡ ወይገብር፡ ተዝካራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ... ወይቄርብ፡ ቍርባነ፡  በበ፡ በዐለ፡ ... ወአልቦቱ፡ ካልአ፡ ምግባረ፡ ሠናየ፡ ኢበውሂበ፡ ምጽዋት፡ ወኢበኂሩት፡  ወመዐትም፡ ብእሲሁ፨ ወአሐተ፡ ዕለተ፡ …
column17: (F. 278ra l. 17) ፸ወ፬፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ … (l. 23) ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእ(f. 278rb)ሲ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ባዕል፡ ጥቀ፡ ወይገብር፡ ተዝካራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም፡ ማሪሃም፡ ወይቄርብ፡ ቍርባነ፡ በበ፡ በዐለ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ማሪሃም፡ ወአልቦቱ፡ ካልአ፡ ምግባረ፡ ሠናየ፡ ኢበውሂበ፡ ምጽዋት፡ ወኢበኂሩት፡ ወመዐትም፡ ብእሲሁ፨ ወአሐተ፡ ዕለተ፡ …
column23: Kropp:A rich man throws harms a beggar but in the name of Mary also gives him a piece of bread. Wounded, bleeding, the beggar eats and praises the rich man. After the death of the rich man, this "good" act is enough for Mary to rescue him from hell;  miracle no. 74 does not match the Vat. Arabic ms f 127, thus must be indigenous to Ethiopia; exemplary miracle for the Kidanä Mǝḥrät Maryam

column4: The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ቀመር፡ ክቡረ፡ ዘመድ፡ ዘስምሰ፡ ክርስቲያናዊ፡ ወኀጢአቱ፡ ዓቢይ፡ ወፍዱል፡ እምኀጢአተ፡ ኵሉ፡ ሰብእ፡ ወባዕል፡ ፈድፋደ፨ ወኢይበልዕ፡ እክለ፡ ወኢሥጋ፡ ላህም፡ ወእንስሳ፨ አላ፡ ይበልዕ፡ ሥጋ፡ ሰብእ፡ ወዘበልዐሰ፡ ሰብእ፡ የአክሉ፡ ፸ወ፰፡ ነፍስ፨ ወኀልቁ፡ ወተወድኡ፡ ዓርካኒሁ፡ ወፍቁራኒሁ፡ …
column17: (F. 279rb l. 14) ፸ወ፭፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ … (l. 20) ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ቀመር፡ ክቡረ፡ ዘመድ፡ ዘስምሰ፡ ክርስቲያናዊ፡ ወኀጢአቱ፡ (f. 279va) ዓቢይ፡ ወፍዱል፡ እምኀጢአተ፡ ኵሉ፡ ሰብእ፡ ወባዕል፡ ፈድፋደ፨ ወኢይበልዕ፡ እክለ፡ ወኢሥጋ፡ ላህም፡ ወእንስሳ፨ አላ፡ ይበልዕ፡ ሥጋ፡ ሰብእ፡ ወዘበልዐሰ፡ ሰብእ፡ የአክሉ፡ ፸ወ፰፡ ነፍስ፨ ወኀልቁ፡ ወተወድኡ፡ ዓርካኒሁ፡ ወፍቁራኒሁ፡ …
column18: Place name: ቀመር፡.
column23: Kropp: the cannibal of Qemer, miracle no. 75; not in Vatican Arabic MS 170, f. 128v, thus must be indigenous to Ethiopia; exemplary miracle for the Kidanä Mǝḥrät Maryam

column4: Saint Basil cycle: Saint Basil and the rich man who refused to give him a tablet [saleda] for an icon of Saint Mary.
Archbishop Tilas, who was seized by Jews while carrying a golden chalice.
The brother of Emperor Constantine who wanted to marry the empress while Constantine was on pilgrimage to Jerusalem.
The church of Saint Mary in Spain to which she used to bring Christian captives.
Holy Family journey cycle: The people of an Egyptian town set fierce dogs on the Holy Family.
Holy Family journey cycle: The inhabitants of an Egyptian town who plot to hand Jesus over to King Herod are turned into animals.
Holy Family journey cycle: The king of Egypt asks Saint Mary to bless his land.
Saint Mary turns water over which her anaphora was recited by Abba Samuˀel of Wali into miraculous bread.
An Egyptian woman comes to Saint Mary in Bethlehem and is healed of her fever.
Mary, Conception of cycle: The descent of the holy seed from Adam to Saint Mary.
The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
The deacon's prayer that contained five times "Rejoice!" [tafassehiyat].
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The five sorrows of Saint Mary.
The story of the blind priest, Yohannes Bakansi; Mary heals his eyes with milk from her breasts
Elizabeth, the blind daughter of Abraham and Gera Anest of Baderman.
The widow who could not find husbands for her three daughters.
The two brothers who copied the Miracles of Mary and fell into the doing of a sin.
Saint Mary appears to the martyr, Giyorgis Haddis, in prison.
The stone-footed man (i. e., a man with gout) from France.
Mary, Dormition of cycle: Christ appears to the Apostles after the Dormition of Saint Mary.
column15: ወእምዝ፡ ተጋብኡ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ኀበ፡ ሀሎ፡ አቡየ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ላዕለ፡ ደብር፡ ወአመሮሙ፡ ኵሎ፡ ዘኮነ፡ በእንተ፡ ሥጋ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ወኃዘኑ፡ በእንተ፡ ዘኢዓርጉ፡ ምስሌሁ፡ ውስተ፡ ገነት፡ ይርአዩ፡ ዘርእየ፡ ዮሐንስ

column4: The story of the icon of Saint Mary of Däbrä Sedeneya, attributed to Cyril of Jerusalem.
The sister of Emperor Constantine who prayed to know how Saint Mary bore the Word of God, but then failed to recognize her Son when he appeared to her in church.
The composition of the Wǝddāse Maryam by the Syrian potter.
The rich woman who went with the monks to the manbalis for prayer and there saw a vision of Saint Mary.
column15: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ... ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእ<ት>ነ፡ ማርያም፡ ጸሎታ፡ ወስእለታ፡ የሀሉ፡ ወትረ፡ ምስለ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ዘርአ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ አሜን፨ ተብህለ፡ ሶበ፡ ፈቀዱ፡ አኃው፡ ከመ፡ ይትጋብኡ፡ ውስተ፡ መንበሊስ፡ ተንሥኡ፡ እምአብርፊስ፡ ኀበ፡ መንበሊስ፨

column4: The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
column15: ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእ<ትነ፡> ማርያም፡ ጸሎታ፡ ወስእለታ፡ የሀሉ፡ ወትረ፡ ምስለ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ዘርአ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ አሜን፨ ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ገበራዊ፡ ዘኮነ፡ ያወትር፡ ኵሎ፡ ዕለተ፡ ሰላማ፡ ለእግዝእት<ነ፡>፡ ማርያም፡ ሰርከ፡ ወነግሀ፡ ወመንፈቀ፡ ማዓልት፨
column23: ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእ<ትነ፡> ማርያም፡ ጸሎታ፡ ወስእለታ፡ የሀሉ፡ ወትረ፡ ምስለ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ዘርአ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ አሜን፨ ወሀሎ፡ አሐዱ፡ ብእሲ፡ ገበራዊ፡ (sic) ዘኮነ፡ ያወትር፡ ኵሎ፡ ዕለተ፡ ሰላማ፡ ለእግዝእት<ነ፡>፡ ማርያም፡ ሰርከ፡ ወነግሀ፡ ወመንፈቀ፡ ማዓልት፨ (sic)

column4: The peasant who became rich from other people's goods.
column15: ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእ<ግ>ዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ጸሎታ፡ ይመግቦ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ ዘ<ር>አ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ አሜን። ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ገባር፡ ባዕል፡ ውእቱ፨ ወባሕቱ፡ ብዕሉኒ፡ ኮነ፡ እምዐመፃ፡

column4: A child and his mother see the icon of Saint Mary weeping for the sins of the world.
A woman whose right eye had been blinded by a demon is healed by Saint Mary.
Saint Mary gives a garment to a poor monk.
The monastic community that was supplied with provisions by Saint Mary.
Saint Mary appears to the martyr, Giyorgis Haddis, in prison.
The daughter of the rich man from Caesarea who could not deliver her baby.
The rich man who threw dry bread to a beggar in the name of Saint Mary.
The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
The young man who used to bring roses to the icon of Saint Mary.
The pilgrim to Santiago whom Satan persuaded to mutilate himself after falling into a sexual sin.
The priest who could only say the Mass of the Virgin Mary.
The widow who prayed to Saint Mary and saved her only son from death by hanging.
The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
Saint Mary appears to an official who kidnapped a girl that had made a vow of virginity.
Saint Mary gives a garment to a poor monk.
An Egyptian woman comes to Saint Mary in Bethlehem and is healed of her fever.
column15: እምብዙሕ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለዲተ፤ አምላክ፨ ... ወመጽአት፤ አሐቲ፤ ብእሲት፤ እምድረ፡ ግብጽ፤ እንዘ፤ ሀለወት፤ እግዝእትነ፤ ቅድስት፤ ድንግል፤ በክልኤ፤ ማርያም፤ ወለዲተ፤ አምላክ፨ በቤተ፤ ልሔም፤ እንዘ፡ ትፈጽን፤ ዓቢየ፤ ፈጸንት፨
column23: Possibly copied from Vatican City, Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana, Aeth. 54, Miracle of Mary: Miracle of an Egyptian woman healed by Mary from fever. Tanśǝʾa Wald is mentioned in the supplication formula at the end of the text. እምብዙሕ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለዲተ፤ (sic) አምላክ፨ ... ወመጽአት፤ አሐቲ፤ ብእሲት፤ እምድረ፡ ግብጽ፤ እንዘ፤ ሀለወት፤ እግዝእትነ፤ ቅድስት፤ ድንግል፤ በክልኤ፤ ማርያም፤ ወለዲተ፤ (sic) አምላክ፨ በቤተ፤ ልሔም፤ እንዘ፡ ትፈጽን፤ ዓቢየ፤ ፈጸንት፨ (sic)

column4: The church built on the tomb of Saint Mary that will turn into a ship.
column15: <እ> ምብዙሕ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ... ስምዑኬ፤ አኃውየ፤ ዘንተ፤ ምስጢረ፤ መንክረ፤ ወመድምመ፤ ዘነገሩነ፤ አበዊነ፤ ቅዱሳን፤ ዘረከብዎ፤ ጽሑፍ፤ ውስተ፤ መጽሐፍት፨ ወይቤሉ፤ አመ፤ ይመጽእ፤ እግዚእነ፤ በዳግም፤ ምጽአቱ፤ በዓቢይ፤ ስብሐት፤ ምስለ፤ መለእክት፤ ወኃይለት፨ ወበንፍሐተ፤ ቀርን፤ ወይትነስኡ፤ ሙታን፤
column23: <እ> ምብዙሕ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ... ስምዑኬ፤ አኃውየ፤ ዘንተ፤ ምስጢረ፤ መንክረ፤ ወመድምመ፤ ዘነገሩነ፤ አበዊነ፤ ቅዱሳን፤ ዘረከብዎ፤ ጽሑፍ፤ ውስተ፤ መጽሐፍት፨ (sic) ወይቤሉ፤ አመ፤ ይመጽእ፤ እግዚእነ፤ በዳግም፤ ምጽአቱ፤ በዓቢይ፤ ስብሐት፤ ምስለ፤ መለእክት፤ (sic) ወኃይለት፨ (sic) ወበንፍሐተ፤ ቀርን፤ ወይትነስኡ፤ ሙታን፤

column4: The two women who were attacked by robbers on their way to church.
column15: እምብዙሕ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ... ወሀለዋ፤ ክልኤቱ፤ አንስት፤ አዕማተ፤ እግዝእትነ፤ ቅድስት፤ ድንግል፤ በክልኤ፤ ማርያም። ወለዲተ፤ አምላክ፤ በቤተ፤ ልሔም፤ እምአዋልድ፤ ይሁዳ፨ ቀአሐተ፤ ዕለተ፤ እንዘ፤ የሐወራ፤ ኢየሩሳሌም፤ ይስግዳ፤ ለብዓለ፤ ፍልሰታ፤ ለእግዝእትነ፤ ቅድስት፤ ድንግል፤ በክልኤ፨ ማርያም፡ ወለዲተ፤ አምለክ፨ ዐገትዎን፤ ፈያት፤ በውስተ፤ ፍኖት፤ ወነስእዎን፤ ስንቆን፤ ለዮልያና፤ ወለበርባራ፤ አዕማተ፤ እግዝእትነ፤
column23: እምብዙሕ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ... ወሀለዋ፤ ክልኤቱ፤ አንስት፤ አዕማተ፤ እግዝእትነ፤ ቅድስት፤ ድንግል፤ በክልኤ፤ ማርያም። ወለዲተ፤ (sic) አምላክ፤ በቤተ፤ ልሔም፤ እምአዋልድ፤ ይሁዳ፨ ቀአሐተ፤ ዕለተ፤ እንዘ፤ የሐወራ፤ (sic) ኢየሩሳሌም፤ ይስግዳ፤ ለብዓለ፤ (sic) ፍልሰታ፤ ለእግዝእትነ፤ ቅድስት፤ ድንግል፤ በክልኤ፨ ማርያም፡ ወለዲተ፤ (sic) አምለክ፨ (sic) ዐገትዎን፤ ፈያት፤ በውስተ፤ ፍኖት፤ ወነስእዎን፤ ስንቆን፤ ለዮልያና፤ ወለበርባራ፤ አዕማተ፤ እግዝእትነ፤

column17: ወሀለዉ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ፪አኃው፡ ፍቁራን፡ ወይትፋቀሩ፡ በበይናቲሆሙ፡ ወየአምሩ፡ ጺሒፈ፡ ወመጽአ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ኀበ፡ እምኔሆሙ፡ ወሰአሎ፡ ከመ፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ሎቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡...

column4: Katir, the old priest from Elkesus, who was about to be dismissed from the church.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ሀገረ፡  ዘይሰመይ፡ እልኩስ፡ ብእሲ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ከጢሮ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስትያኖ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡… ወባቲ፡ ለይእቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዓቃቤ፡ ዘእኩይ፡ ግዕዙ። ወይቤሎ፡ ለቀሲስ፡ እንተ፡ ትንብር፡ ዝየ፡
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ሀገረ፡  ዘይሰመይ፡ እልኩስ፡ ብእሲ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ከጢሮ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስትያኖ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ወባቲ፡ ለይእቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዓቃቤ፡ ዘእኩይ፡ ግዕዙ። ወይቤሎ፡ ለቀሲስ፡ እንተ፡ ትንብር፡ ዝየ፡
column23: Solomon says 82, but not ITool result, because ከጢር not ከጢሮ and a few other reasons, but 82 is correct

column4: Saint Mary appears to the martyr, Giyorgis Haddis, in prison.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ሐዲስ፡ መስተጋድል፡ ፈድፋደ፡ ለክዊነ፡ ስምዕ፡ ለክርስቶስ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ወዝንቱ፡ ጻድቅ፡ ውስተ፡ ማሕበረ፡ ምኵናን፡

column4: The story of the two brothers from Dalga who were dyers.
column15: ወሀለው፡ ፪ አኃው፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ዘስሙ፡ ደልይ፡ እለ፡ የአልሉ፡ አልባሰ፡ በቀለመ፡ ኒል፡ ፩ቀሲስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ታግ፡

column4: The stone-footed man (i. e., a man with gout) from France.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ዘብሔረ፡ አፍርንጊ፡ ዘዕብን፡ እግሩ፡ ወውእቱ፡ ከይሲ፡ ይከድን፡ እግሮ፡ በልብስ፡ ከመ፡ ኢያዕምሮ፡ ሰብእ፡ ይበኪ፡ ወያስቆቁ፡ መዓልተ፡ ወለሊተ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ እረፍት፡:..

column4: Bishop Mercurius, whom the patriarch wanted to remove because of leprosy.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ መርቆሬዎስ፡ ዘኮነ፡ ለምጸ፡ ኵሉ፡ ሥጋሁ፡ ወአሐቲ፡ ዕለተ፡ ሖረ፡ ኀበ፡ ዘካርያስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ወሶበ፡ ርእየ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ገሠጾ፡ ወይቤሎ፡ በትህትና፡

column4: A poor woman with a broken leg is healed by the icon of Saint Mary in the church of Harat ar-Rum.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ በሀገረ፡ ሀርተሎም፡ ወሀለወት፡ውስቴቱ፡ ሥዕለ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡… ዘይሰመይዋ፡ ረድኤተ፡ወአሐቲ፡ ነዳይት፡ ዘተሰብረት፡ እግራ፡
column17: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ በሀገረ፡ ሀርተሎም፡ ወሀለወት፡ውስቴቱ፡ ሥዕለ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ዘይሰመይዋ፡ ረድኤተ፡ወአሐቲ፡ ነዳይት፡ ዘተሰብረት፡ እግራ፡

column4: The prioress who became pregnant after sinning with a servant.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ በደብረ፡ ቀርሜሎስ፡ዘስማ፡ ሶፍያ፡ዘሠናይ፡ ግዕዘ፡ ወትፈርሆ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ወታፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡… በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወሀለዋ፡ውስተ፡ ውእቱ፡ ድብራ፡  ደናግል፡
column17: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ በደብረ፡ ቀርሜሎስ፡ዘስማ፡ ሶፍያ፡ዘሠናይ፡ ግዕዘ፡ ወትፈርሆ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ወታፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወሀለዋ፡ውስተ፡ ውእቱ፡ ድብራ፡  ደናግል፡

column4: The sinful deacon whom his enemies could not kill until he had confessed himself to a priest.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ እኩይ፡ በሀገረ፡ ፊንቂስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ባሮክ፡ ጠዋይ፡ ወአልቦቱ፡ ምግባረ፡ ሠናይ፡ ወኢያዕምሮ፡ ለእግዚአብሐር፡ ወኮነ፡ ጽሉእ፡ ወምኑነ፡ በኀበ፡ ኵሎሙ፡
ወሀሎ፡ ዲያቆን፡ ዘስሙ፡ ኦንሶጣስዮስ፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፡ ዘበራንጥያን፡  ወፈራኄ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ውእቱ፡ ወያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡… ወይገይሰ፡ ወትረ፡...
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ዲያቆን፡ ዘስሙ፡ ኦንሶጣስዮስ፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮሜ፡ ዘበራንጥያን፡  ወፈራኄ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ውእቱ፡ ወያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ወይገይሰ፡ ወትረ፡...

column4: Dabra Qaləmon miracles: The monk of Dabra Qaləmon who humbly pretends not to fast and is saved from his brothers by Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩መነኮስ፡ በደብረ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ ዘቀልሞስ፡ ወያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡… ወያነብብ፡ ወትረ፡
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩መነኮስ፡ በደብረ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ ዘቀልሞስ፡ ወያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡. ወያነብብ፡ ወትረ፡

column4: The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡  በሀገረ፡ ቅምር፡ ክቡረ፡ ዘመድ፡ በስም፡ ክርስቲያናዊ፡ ወኃጢያቱሰ፡ ዓቢይ፡ ፈድፋደ፡ እምኃጢያተ፡ ኵሉ፡አለም፡ ወኢይበልዕ፡ እክለ፡ ወኢሥጋ፡ ላህም፡

column4: The thief who was caught stealing from the church of Saint Mary and was released by his captors when he prayed to her.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ሠራቂ፡ ወቀሣጢ፡ ቢተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወኵሎ፡ አሚረ፡ ነበረ፡ እንዘ፡ ይቀስጥ፡ እስመ፡ እኩየ፡ ልማድ፡.

column4: A barren woman conceives and bears salda Masqal.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ዘአልጸቀት፡ ለወሊድ። ወእንዘ፡ ተሐውር፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡  ክርስቲያን፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ለግቢረ፡ በዓል፡ምስለ፡ ብዙኃን፡ ሰብእ፡

column4: Saint Mary gives a thirsty dog water to drink from her shoe.
column15: ወሀለዋ፡ ፪አንስት፡ ምስለ፡ እግዝእትነ፡… ወመጽአት፡ ክልብ፡ ጽሙሰ፡ ወሰደድሁ፡ ውእቶን፡  አንስት፡  ወእግዝእትነሰ፡ አስተእጸበት፡.
column17: ወሀለዋ፡ ፪አንስት፡ ምስለ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ወመጽአት፡ ክልብ፡ ጽሙሰ፡ ወሰደድሁ፡ ውእቶን፡  አንስት፡  ወእግዝእትነሰ፡ አስተእጸበት፡.

column4: Holy Family journey cycle: The rich Egyptian woman who refused to give water to the Holy Family.
column15: ወኮነ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ነገር፡ እምድህረ፡ ወለድቶ፡  ለእግዚእትነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አዘዘ፡ ኄሮድስ፡ ከመ፡ ይቅትሉ፡ ሕፃናተ፡ ዘ፪፡ ዓመት፡ ወዘይንእስ፡ ወሰሚዓ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ አጐየቶ፡ ለወልዳ፡ እስመ፡ ጊዜ፡ ቀትር፡ ወእቱ፡ ወአንበረቶ፡ ለሕፃን፡ ውስተ፤ ጽንፈ ፡ ሀገር፡
ተብህለ፡ ኮነ፡ ከመ፡  ሀሎ፡ ፩መነኮስ፡ ዘአልቦቱ፡ ሲሳየ፡ ወልብስ፡ ወይትአመና፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡… ወይብል፡ ኵሎ፡ እለተ፡ ለለጊዜ፡ አዚዝ፡ ሲተ፡ ለእለብስ፡

column23: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ባዕል፡ ጥቀ፡ ወይገብር፡ ተዝካራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ወይቄርብ፡ ቁርባነ፡ በበአለ፡ ወአልቦቱ፡ ካልአ፡ ምግባረ፡ ሠናይ፡ ኢበውሂበ፡ ምጽዋት፡

column4: The story of the cannibal from Qemer.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ በሀገረ፡ ቅምር፡ ክቡረ፡ ዘመድ፡ ወስሙሰ፡ ክርስቲያናዊ፡ ወኃጥአቱዕ፡ ዓቢይ፡ ወፍዱል፡ እምኃጥያተ፡ ኩሉ፡ ሰብእ፡ ወባዕል፡ ፈድፋደ፡ ወኢይበልዕ፡ ዕክለ፡ ወኢሥጋ

column4: The composition of the Miracles of Mary by Bishop Hildephonsus of Toledo.
column15: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘሀገረ፡ ጥልጥልያ፡ ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶስ፡  ዘስሙ፡ ደቅስዮስ። ወኮነ፡ ብእሲ፡ ብሩክ፡ ወኄር፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ... በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወይትለአክ፡ በኵሉ፡ ኃይሉ፡...
column17: ተብህለ፡ ከመ፡ ሀሎ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘሀገረ፡ ጥልጥልያ፡ ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶስ፡  ዘስሙ፡ ደቅስዮስ። ወኮነ፡ ብእሲ፡ ብሩክ፡ ወኄር፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ በኵሉ፡ ልቡ፡ ወይትለአክ፡ በኵሉ፡ ኃይሉ፡...
column36: How the Virgin Mary accepted the book of her miracles compiled by Saint Hildefonsus [Däqsəyos], Bishop of Toledo (Budge, Mary 1; Strelcyn 15.1.1, 32.16.1; also commonly first in medieval European collections).

column4: The monk who has carried by the bretheren to church when he became too sick to walk.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ ደብረ፡ መነኮሳት፡ በደሴተ፡ ጤግሮስ፡ ዘይሰመይ፡ ደብረ፡ ኤፍሬም፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡...። ወኢያንትክ፡ገይሠ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያ፡ ወይሁብ፡ ሰላመ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ።...
column17: ወሀለወት፡ ደብረ፡ መነኮሳት፡ በደሴተ፡ ጤግሮስ፡ ዘይሰመይ፡ ደብረ፡ ኤፍሬም፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ። ወኢያንትክ፡ገይሠ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያ፡ ወይሁብ፡ ሰላመ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ።...
column36: How the Virgin Mary appeared to the dying monk in island of Tigris) (not in Budge).

column4: The peasant who complained to Saint Mary because she did not reply to his Hail Mary.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ገባራዊ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡... በኵሉ፡ ልቡ። ወያወትር፡ አንብቦተ፡ ሰላማ፡ ለለዕለቱ፡ ነግዐ፡ ወቀትረ፡ ወምሴተ፡ ወነበረ፡ ከመዝ፡ ብዙኃ፡ መዋዕለ።..
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ገባራዊ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ በኵሉ፡ ልቡ። ወያወትር፡ አንብቦተ፡ ሰላማ፡ ለለዕለቱ፡ ነግዐ፡ ወቀትረ፡ ወምሴተ፡ ወነበረ፡ ከመዝ፡ ብዙኃ፡ መዋዕለ።..
column36: How the Virgin Mary spoke from her picture to a devout worshipper) (Budge, Mary 2; Strelcyn 15.1.3, 32.16.2).

column4: The pious monk (or: the Jew from Akhmim) whom Saint Mary made young.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ዕብራዊ፡ በሀገረ፡ አክሚም፡  ዘያፈቅራ፡ ... እምሥርወ፡ ልቡ፡ ወኢያጸርዕ፡ እማአፉሁ፡ ዝክረ፡ ስማ፡ በፍርሃት፡ ብዙኅ፡ ወበረዓድ። ወበጊዜ፡ ይሰግድሂ፡ ላቲ፡ ይኤምኅ፡ ምድረ፡ በእንተ፡ ክብረ፡ ስማ።...
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ዕብራዊ፡ በሀገረ፡ አክሚም፡  ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ እምሥርወ፡ ልቡ፡ ወኢያጸርዕ፡ እማአፉሁ፡ ዝክረ፡ ስማ፡ በፍርሃት፡ ብዙኅ፡ ወበረዓድ። ወበጊዜ፡ ይሰግድሂ፡ ላቲ፡ ይኤምኅ፡ ምድረ፡ በእንተ፡ ክብረ፡ ስማ።...
column36: How the Virgin Mary healed the Jew of Akəmim, an elderly priest, when he fell and broke his back during his service in her church) (Budge, Mary, 3).

column4: The pious monk scribe who used to write Saint Mary's name in golden ink.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ዘይነብር፡ በሀገረ፡ ፊልጵስዩስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ድምያኖስ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ... እማዕምቀ፡ ልቡ፡ ወይትለአክ፡ በኵሉ፡  ክኂሎቱ፡ ወይተግህ፡ መዓልተ፡ ወሌሊተ፡...
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ዘይነብር፡ በሀገረ፡ ፊልጵስዩስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ድምያኖስ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ እማዕምቀ፡ ልቡ፡ ወይትለአክ፡ በኵሉ፡  ክኂሎቱ፡ ወይተግህ፡ መዓልተ፡ ወሌሊተ፡...
column36: How the Virgin Mary appeared to the dying scribe Damianus) (Budge, Mary, 4).

column4: The Muslim whom Saint Mary told to receive baptism. Later, as Bishop of Rome, he cut off his hand because of a carnal thought.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ እምጳጳሳተ፡ ሮሜ፡ ዘይብልዎ፡ አባሰ፡ እምጳጳሳት፡ ወኄር፡ውእቱ፡ብእሲ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወይፈርሆ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር። ወየዓቅብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ እምዝሙት፡ ወእምሕሊና፡ እኩይ። ወአሐተ፡ ዕለተ፡ ...
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ እምጳጳሳተ፡ ሮሜ፡ ዘይብልዎ፡ አባሰ፡ እምጳጳሳት፡ ወኄር፡ውእቱ፡ብእሲ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወይፈርሆ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር። ወየዓቅብ፡ ነፍሶ፡ እምዝሙት፡ ወእምሕሊና፡ እኩይ። ወአሐተ፡ ዕለተ፡ ...
column36: How Abbas, Bishop of Rome, cut off his hand which had been kissed by a woman when he was celebrating the Eucharist, andHow the Virgin Mary rejoined it to his arm) (Budge, Mary, 5).

column4: The monk, Yǝsḥaq, who prayed for seven years that Saint Mary would appear to him.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩መነኮስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ይስሐቅ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ... በኵሉ፡ ልቡ። ወእምንዕሱ፡ ነበረ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ደብር፡ በመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለአባ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡...
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩መነኮስ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ይስሐቅ፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ በኵሉ፡ ልቡ። ወእምንዕሱ፡ ነበረ፡ ውስተ፡ አሐቲ፡ ደብር፡ በመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለአባ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡...
column36: How the Virgin Mary appeared to Isaac, the elderly monk, and promised to take him to herself after three days) (Budge, Mary, 6).

column4: Maryam from Dǝfrā, a child who wanted to receive Communion but was shut up in the house when her family went to church, goes to heaven.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ፋራሄ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡... ። ወሀገሩሰ፡ ድፍራ፡ ወአውሰበ፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ወወለደ፡ እምኔሃ፡ ፫ውሉደ፡ ፪ተ፡ ተባዕተ፡ ወአሐተ፡ ወለተ፡...
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ፋራሄ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ። ወሀገሩሰ፡ ድፍራ፡ ወአውሰበ፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ወወለደ፡ እምኔሃ፡ ፫ውሉደ፡ ፪ተ፡ ተባዕተ፡ ወአሐተ፡ ወለተ፡...
column36: How the Virgin Mary appeared out of her picture to Mary, the daughter of a certain God-fearing man, and promised to take her to Paradise after three days) (Budge, Mary, 7; Strelcyn 32.16.7).

column4: The French artist who fell from the scaffolding while painting frescoes.
column15: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ሠዓሊ፡ አልቦ፡ ዘይትማሰሎ፡ በውእቱ፡ አዝማን፡ በገቢረ፡ ሥዕል። ወያፈቅራ፡ ...። ወሶበ፡ ይገብር፡ ሥዕላ፡ በተናቅቆ፡ ወበብዙኅ፡ ፃህቅ፡ ይሥእል፡...
column17: ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ሠዓሊ፡ አልቦ፡ ዘይትማሰሎ፡ በውእቱ፡ አዝማን፡ በገቢረ፡ ሥዕል። ወያፈቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ በ፪ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ። ወሶበ፡ ይገብር፡ ሥዕላ፡ በተናቅቆ፡ ወበብዙኅ፡ ፃህቅ፡ ይሥእል፡...
column36: How a painter was saved by the Virgin Mary when he fell from a scaffold) (Budge, Mary, 8, Strelcyn ??).

column4: Saint Mary carries a dying monk to Jerusalem.
column15: ወሀለወት፡ ሥዕለ፡ ... በደብረ፡ ነጋድያን፡ በቤተ፡ ሕሙማን፡ መንገለ፡ ምስራቅ፡ ዘለለጽባሑ፡ ይትመሐፀኑ፡ ባቲ፡  ሕሙማን።  ወሀሎ፡ ህየ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡..
